1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:17,984
A makeover project
for your most unhinged leftovers.

2
00:00:18,051 --> 00:00:21,321
The best chefs in Korea will
turn your fridge inside out.

3
00:00:21,388 --> 00:00:23,656
The classy cooking show has returned.

4
00:00:23,723 --> 00:00:27,093
<i>-Chef & My Fridge!</i>
<i>-My Fridge!</i>

5
00:00:28,128 --> 00:00:29,129
Great to see you all.

6
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:31,631
LOOKING FORWARD TO ANOTHER GREAT EPISODE

7
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:34,100
-She's here yet again.
-She is.

8
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:37,704
The chef who managed to destroy Eun-yeong
on her first day.

9
00:00:37,971 --> 00:00:39,773
SHOWED HER JUNIOR CHINESE CHEF
WHO THE BOSS IS

10
00:00:39,839 --> 00:00:42,542
Please welcome Witch With a Wok,
Chef Yi Moon-jung.

11
00:00:42,609 --> 00:00:45,512
I heard you couldn't sleep well
after the previous shoot.

12
00:00:45,578 --> 00:00:49,816
It was very thrilling to make something
within just 15 minutes.

13
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:52,719
It gave me a huge dopamine hit.

14
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,822
-On top of that…
-It gets your heart racing.

15
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:57,323
…I won against my junior chef

16
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:58,658
and got to save face.

17
00:00:58,725 --> 00:00:59,993
A HEARTY LAUGH

18
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,328
-She showed what she was capable of.
-Oh, no, Eun-yeong.

19
00:01:02,395 --> 00:01:03,663
She's done for.

20
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:06,299
-I'll do my best today as well.
-She sounds like a soldier.

21
00:01:06,366 --> 00:01:08,468
-Like a Special Forces soldier.
-Yes, the Special Forces.

22
00:01:08,535 --> 00:01:10,770
After the previous shoot,

23
00:01:10,837 --> 00:01:14,541
the other chefs who were here with her
had nothing but good things to say.

24
00:01:14,707 --> 00:01:15,775
IT'S TRUE!

25
00:01:16,009 --> 00:01:17,877
THANK YOU

26
00:01:17,944 --> 00:01:20,380
When I heard she'd be here,
I thought of my first day

27
00:01:20,447 --> 00:01:22,415
and wanted to look after her,

28
00:01:22,482 --> 00:01:24,451
thinking I should help out.

29
00:01:24,517 --> 00:01:26,619
But rather, I was the one left in shock.

30
00:01:26,686 --> 00:01:29,422
<i>Not only was she good at cooking,</i>

31
00:01:29,489 --> 00:01:31,491
I didn't expect her
to dance with double knives

32
00:01:31,558 --> 00:01:33,159
-Even Eun-yeong was surprised.
-She was.

33
00:01:33,226 --> 00:01:35,995
-And that was her first day.
-Has Chef Eun-yeong lost her spot?

34
00:01:36,062 --> 00:01:37,397
She's on her honeymoon.

35
00:01:37,464 --> 00:01:39,165
-She's now in Hawaii.
-She's in Hawaii.

36
00:01:39,232 --> 00:01:41,367
She made a big scene,
saying she'll come to the shoot

37
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:43,269
instead of going on her trip.

38
00:01:43,336 --> 00:01:45,872
Apparently, she demanded
that they let her off the plane.

39
00:01:45,939 --> 00:01:47,540
She knows she's in jeopardy.

40
00:01:47,607 --> 00:01:49,542
We don't usually message each other,

41
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:53,580
but she contacted me and asked
if the shooting date hasn't changed,

42
00:01:53,646 --> 00:01:55,648
who the guests were,

43
00:01:55,715 --> 00:01:58,718
if Chef Moon-jung was coming.
She had many questions.

44
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:02,188
Chef Moon-jung, why don't you leave
a word for Eun-yeong today?

45
00:02:02,255 --> 00:02:03,690
Eun-yeong.

46
00:02:03,756 --> 00:02:05,191
I'm back.

47
00:02:05,658 --> 00:02:07,861
AIR HORN

48
00:02:07,927 --> 00:02:08,828
"I've taken your spot."

49
00:02:08,895 --> 00:02:11,464
I heard you went to Hawaii
for your honeymoon trip.

50
00:02:11,531 --> 00:02:13,766
You should stay for a year.

51
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,135
WELL-WISHES FROM YOUR SENIOR

52
00:02:15,201 --> 00:02:16,503
A year's too long.

53
00:02:16,569 --> 00:02:18,404
I'll hold the fort down,

54
00:02:18,471 --> 00:02:20,406
so enjoy your honeymoon

55
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:22,709
because you've earned it, Eun-yeong.

56
00:02:23,009 --> 00:02:24,177
CHORTLE

57
00:02:24,244 --> 00:02:25,612
-She's been struggling.
-Hawaii's great.

58
00:02:25,678 --> 00:02:28,481
Sung-jun is the only one
who isn't smiling right now.

59
00:02:28,548 --> 00:02:29,983
-What's up?
-Why, Sung-jun?

60
00:02:30,049 --> 00:02:31,784
I have a feeling that I'm next.

61
00:02:32,685 --> 00:02:34,487
-I'm a bit scared.
-For now…

62
00:02:34,554 --> 00:02:37,891
-I had a whole different thought.
-You did?

63
00:02:37,957 --> 00:02:39,659
When this show first began,

64
00:02:39,726 --> 00:02:41,427
there was a chef who stole the whole show,

65
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:44,030
hurling salt into his food,
displaying a fancy performance.

66
00:02:44,097 --> 00:02:48,234
If he was only funny,
he could've ended as a laughingstock,

67
00:02:48,301 --> 00:02:50,470
but he had the skills
to back up his silliness,

68
00:02:50,537 --> 00:02:54,574
so people showed him respect
and loved watching him, right?

69
00:02:54,641 --> 00:02:57,177
She reminded me of my early days.

70
00:02:57,243 --> 00:02:59,078
In a nutshell, you're showing off again.

71
00:02:59,345 --> 00:03:01,247
AS ALWAYS…

72
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:03,216
-What did Sam say?
-He said,

73
00:03:04,050 --> 00:03:05,251
"He's just a laughingstock."

74
00:03:05,985 --> 00:03:07,353
BECOMING THE LAUGHINGSTOCK

75
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:09,088
EVIL SAM'S FIRST WORD OF THE DAY

76
00:03:09,155 --> 00:03:10,156
That's all he said today.

77
00:03:10,223 --> 00:03:13,459
I need to have a chat with you two
after this shoot.

78
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:15,094
He's the drill sergeant of the line.

79
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:18,031
OUR TWISTED DRILL SERGEANT

80
00:03:18,097 --> 00:03:22,669
Last time, Hyun-suk lost the cook-off and
had to write nice comments for Ho-young.

81
00:03:22,735 --> 00:03:25,538
But if I win, Chef Hyun-suk
must like my posts

82
00:03:25,605 --> 00:03:27,006
and leave a comment.

83
00:03:27,273 --> 00:03:29,442
JUNG HO-YOUNG WINS

84
00:03:29,709 --> 00:03:32,111
HYUN-SUK MUST WRITE NICE COMMENTS
ON HO-YOUNG'S POSTS

85
00:03:32,178 --> 00:03:33,279
SIGH

86
00:03:33,346 --> 00:03:34,247
It's a bit…

87
00:03:34,314 --> 00:03:36,149
<i>Since that day, Chef Ho-young has been…</i>

88
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:37,617
FOR A WEEK STARTING TODAY, HYUN-SUK

89
00:03:37,684 --> 00:03:40,186
<i>…posting like crazy on his account.</i>

90
00:03:40,253 --> 00:03:41,988
<i>-He's way too excited.</i>
<i>-After he won?</i>

91
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:44,290
<i>-At least 30 posts, I think.</i>
<i>-In that short while?</i>

92
00:03:44,357 --> 00:03:47,527
I've been tagging him in case
he misses them and forgets to comment.

93
00:03:47,594 --> 00:03:49,529
He's pretty much my co-uploader.

94
00:03:49,596 --> 00:03:50,897
That's why you're tagging him?

95
00:03:50,964 --> 00:03:53,967
PROVING HIS EXPERTISE
AS THE SOCIAL MEDIA ADDICT OF THE SHOW

96
00:03:54,033 --> 00:03:56,336
I hear you're considering
deleting your account.

97
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:57,770
-Really?
-It's that hard?

98
00:03:57,837 --> 00:04:00,974
He has to leave a comment,
so he's doing his best to say something.

99
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,842
His efforts are heartbreaking.

100
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:04,510
SCAN TO CHECK OUT ALL HIS COMMENTS

101
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:08,147
-I hear you want to make another bet.
-Is that so?

102
00:04:08,214 --> 00:04:10,550
-I'll bet a month of comments,
-A month?

103
00:04:10,617 --> 00:04:14,087
-…and him, deactivating his account.
-Deactivating?

104
00:04:14,153 --> 00:04:16,656
-Permanent deletion.
-Deleting the account.

105
00:04:16,889 --> 00:04:18,091
ARE YOU IN?

106
00:04:18,157 --> 00:04:20,627
That's as bad as leaving the show.

107
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:23,563
WILL THE DRILL SERGEANT
PUT HO-YOUNG THROUGH A DIGITAL DETOX?

108
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:26,566
We're now about to meet

109
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:31,371
the fridge owners who are here
to put their trust in our chefs.

110
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:34,107
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

111
00:04:34,173 --> 00:04:35,308
Come on out!

112
00:04:36,342 --> 00:04:37,910
STILL FASCINATED

113
00:04:39,145 --> 00:04:41,014
Today's fridge owners!

114
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:45,018
-Welcome.
-Namkoong Min and Kim Dae-myung, welcome!

115
00:04:45,084 --> 00:04:47,520
…and Kim Dae-myung, welcome!

116
00:04:48,488 --> 00:04:49,822
Did you trip on something?

117
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:51,891
DIY REPAIR

118
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,092
CUTE

119
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,994
EMBARRASSED

120
00:04:55,061 --> 00:04:57,563
-Hello.
-Hello.

121
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:59,032
Let me introduce them to you.

122
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:01,668
He has won three Grand Prizes in acting
for <i>Stove League</i>,

123
00:05:01,734 --> 00:05:03,636
The Veil<i>, and </i>My Dearest.

124
00:05:03,703 --> 00:05:05,738
Best Actor Award, Namkoong Min.

125
00:05:05,805 --> 00:05:09,609
<i>Also, he won the Best Actor Award</i>
<i>at the Baeksang Arts Awards.</i>

126
00:05:09,676 --> 00:05:12,278
One of the nation's most beloved actors,
Namkoong Min!

127
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:13,646
Hello. It's great to be here.

128
00:05:13,713 --> 00:05:15,315
I look forward to it.

129
00:05:16,916 --> 00:05:18,418
OH, MY♥

130
00:05:18,484 --> 00:05:19,886
You look so great.

131
00:05:19,952 --> 00:05:21,154
Thank you.

132
00:05:21,220 --> 00:05:23,323
I'm captivated by his eyes.

133
00:05:23,389 --> 00:05:24,557
Take a dive, then.

134
00:05:24,624 --> 00:05:25,958
ALLOW ME TO TAKE A QUICK SWIM

135
00:05:26,426 --> 00:05:29,429
-I've already been there.
-I just want to fall into them.

136
00:05:29,495 --> 00:05:31,297
Now, this guy.

137
00:05:31,364 --> 00:05:34,300
-You've shed quite a lot of weight.
-Allow me to introduce him.

138
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:37,670
Just follow this man to see
both talent and great food.

139
00:05:37,737 --> 00:05:40,073
<i>Not only does he show talent within dramas</i>

140
00:05:40,139 --> 00:05:41,874
like <i>Misaeng</i> and <i>Hospital Playlist,</i>

141
00:05:41,941 --> 00:05:43,743
but he also knows
all the good restaurants.

142
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:45,945
Please welcome a down-to-earth actor,
Kim Dae-myung!

143
00:05:46,012 --> 00:05:48,314
-Kim Dae-myung!
-Welcome.

144
00:05:48,381 --> 00:05:51,417
Hello. Thank you for inviting me today.

145
00:05:51,484 --> 00:05:53,953
-Hello.
-You've lost a lot of weight.

146
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:56,789
I either gain or lose weight
depending on the character I'm playing.

147
00:05:56,856 --> 00:05:58,291
NODDING

148
00:05:58,358 --> 00:06:00,460
So even you have to do
something like that?

149
00:06:00,526 --> 00:06:02,362
Well, I was paid, so…

150
00:06:02,862 --> 00:06:04,130
PROFESSIONALISM

151
00:06:04,197 --> 00:06:05,932
You get paid, you deliver.

152
00:06:05,998 --> 00:06:07,834
Do you get paid by kilograms?

153
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:09,268
PAID BY THE KILO?

154
00:06:09,335 --> 00:06:10,737
It's market price, actually.

155
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:12,238
HE'S WILLING TO PLAY ALONG

156
00:06:12,305 --> 00:06:14,307
Market price?

157
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:19,045
They said they've been watching
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> for a very long time

158
00:06:19,112 --> 00:06:21,447
and were quite excited to be here.

159
00:06:21,514 --> 00:06:22,348
It's true.

160
00:06:22,415 --> 00:06:25,184
I love to eat good food,

161
00:06:25,251 --> 00:06:27,320
and whenever I meet chefs like them,

162
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:29,856
I can't help but feel admiration.

163
00:06:29,922 --> 00:06:32,191
So when I thought about
meeting eight of them all at once,

164
00:06:32,258 --> 00:06:34,761
-I was a little nervous.
-I see.

165
00:06:34,827 --> 00:06:35,695
Goodness.

166
00:06:35,762 --> 00:06:38,798
He has a good way with words,

167
00:06:38,865 --> 00:06:41,134
talking with this heartwarming smile.

168
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:44,570
I've always been a huge fan of the show,

169
00:06:44,637 --> 00:06:46,205
so may I go one by one?

170
00:06:46,272 --> 00:06:47,840
-Sure.
-As you wish.

171
00:06:47,907 --> 00:06:51,077
I've known Chef Hyun-suk
since his first salt-hurling days,

172
00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:53,546
so basically,
I've been a fan of the show since then.

173
00:06:53,613 --> 00:06:55,448
CHEF & MY FRIDGE'S GATEWAY MEMBER

174
00:06:56,015 --> 00:06:57,316
As for Webtoon Artist Poong,

175
00:06:57,383 --> 00:06:59,385
-I've made your tomato and egg dish.
-Right.

176
00:06:59,452 --> 00:07:00,853
That was the first season.

177
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,055
It was like discovering a whole new world.

178
00:07:03,122 --> 00:07:04,724
POONG GOT HIM HOOKED ON COOKING

179
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:07,360
Chef Jong-won has shared

180
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:10,062
his go-to restaurants on his social media,

181
00:07:10,129 --> 00:07:11,764
and many of them
were my favorite places too.

182
00:07:11,831 --> 00:07:13,733
THEY HAVE SIMILAR TASTES

183
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,068
-Do you know Chef Moon-jung too?
-Of course!

184
00:07:16,135 --> 00:07:17,870
I've been enjoying your YouTube channel.

185
00:07:18,738 --> 00:07:19,839
I'm flattered.

186
00:07:19,906 --> 00:07:23,176
I've once met Chef Sam
on another occasion,

187
00:07:23,242 --> 00:07:25,912
-and I've been to Ho-young's restaurant.
-Ho-young.

188
00:07:25,978 --> 00:07:27,580
-He's the real deal.
-What about the twins?

189
00:07:27,647 --> 00:07:29,549
I wanted to visit their restaurants,

190
00:07:29,615 --> 00:07:31,617
so I even went to Namyeong-dong
and Sindang-dong.

191
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:34,487
Wait, why are we grouped together?

192
00:07:34,554 --> 00:07:36,122
You went one by one until now.

193
00:07:36,189 --> 00:07:37,857
We're a set.

194
00:07:37,924 --> 00:07:39,792
I want to be a part of your club too.

195
00:07:40,026 --> 00:07:41,828
FROM TUBBY TWINS TO TUBBY TRIPLETS

196
00:07:41,894 --> 00:07:45,364
He must love the show so much
if he took time to mention everyone.

197
00:07:45,431 --> 00:07:47,400
I guess Min doesn't love us that much.

198
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:50,203
You should've put a time limit on him.

199
00:07:50,269 --> 00:07:51,737
Did he go on for too long?

200
00:07:51,804 --> 00:07:55,074
-He's good with words.
-I have things to say too.

201
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:56,876
I can go on and on, even longer than him,

202
00:07:56,943 --> 00:07:58,978
but I cut it short to move things forward.

203
00:07:59,245 --> 00:08:00,913
HE JUST DIDN'T HAVE ENOUGH TIME

204
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:04,517
He's simply holding back his love for us.
Please don't take him the wrong way.

205
00:08:04,584 --> 00:08:08,888
-There's a reason why you came together.
-Yes, that's right.

206
00:08:08,955 --> 00:08:13,092
We're both starring in a show
called <i>The Husband,</i>

207
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,827
which premieres in July.

208
00:08:14,894 --> 00:08:18,064
-Dae-myung and I are in it together.
-July.

209
00:08:18,130 --> 00:08:20,199
I'm someone who loses his wife,

210
00:08:20,266 --> 00:08:22,969
and he's the one who kidnapped her.

211
00:08:23,035 --> 00:08:25,037
-You're a kidnapper?
-He's the villain.

212
00:08:25,104 --> 00:08:27,473
-He kidnapped my wife.
-I see.

213
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:28,774
What an evil man.

214
00:08:28,841 --> 00:08:30,710
He's a really scary guy.

215
00:08:30,776 --> 00:08:33,679
-He's heinous.
-What a heinous character.

216
00:08:33,746 --> 00:08:35,882
But what are the chances?

217
00:08:35,948 --> 00:08:39,051
The drama will be on air
right when this show is on.

218
00:08:39,118 --> 00:08:40,086
The same slot?

219
00:08:40,152 --> 00:08:41,921
-Can he do this?
-It's on the weekends?

220
00:08:41,988 --> 00:08:44,590
But I think <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>

221
00:08:44,657 --> 00:08:46,359
should do better.

222
00:08:46,626 --> 00:08:47,693
AWKWARD ON BOTH ENDS

223
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,195
This is awkward.

224
00:08:49,262 --> 00:08:51,430
Please watch our drama on Saturdays,

225
00:08:51,497 --> 00:08:53,065
and on Sundays,

226
00:08:53,566 --> 00:08:54,767
please tune in.

227
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:58,838
-I left the subject out.
-He left the subject out.

228
00:08:58,905 --> 00:09:02,909
Anyway, Min has won Grand Prizes in acting

229
00:09:02,975 --> 00:09:05,077
for <i>Stove League</i>,

230
00:09:05,144 --> 00:09:06,612
<i>The Veil,</i>

231
00:09:06,679 --> 00:09:08,047
and <i>My Dearest.</i>

232
00:09:08,114 --> 00:09:11,417
Your upcoming project
will be aired on KBS,

233
00:09:11,484 --> 00:09:13,286
so if you win the Grand Prize with this,

234
00:09:13,352 --> 00:09:15,555
you'd be winning it
on all three major TV networks.

235
00:09:15,621 --> 00:09:16,856
-Whoa.
-That's amazing.

236
00:09:16,923 --> 00:09:20,259
I did not choose to work with KBS
because of that.

237
00:09:20,326 --> 00:09:22,161
-That's not the case.
-It's not.

238
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:24,797
But when I got the script

239
00:09:24,864 --> 00:09:27,166
and heard it'd be aired on KBS,

240
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:29,735
it did feel a bit more appealing.

241
00:09:29,802 --> 00:09:32,004
-Of course, you'd think of it.
-It'd be a great record.

242
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:35,942
So if they give it to me,
I'm ready to accept it with gratitude.

243
00:09:36,008 --> 00:09:38,911
Among our chefs, Hyun-suk said

244
00:09:38,978 --> 00:09:41,948
he admires Min very dearly.

245
00:09:42,014 --> 00:09:43,883
-Thank you.
-Is that so?

246
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,117
I was really surprised

247
00:09:45,184 --> 00:09:47,820
when I saw him all bulky on a show.

248
00:09:47,887 --> 00:09:50,122
It was as if he had put on a new body,

249
00:09:50,189 --> 00:09:52,191
because he had become this big.

250
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:56,295
It was as if someone blew air into him
and enlarged his back.

251
00:09:56,362 --> 00:09:58,130
Let's take a look.

252
00:09:58,197 --> 00:09:59,932
<i>Look at that guy.</i>

253
00:09:59,999 --> 00:10:01,400
It was during <i>The Veil</i>.

254
00:10:01,467 --> 00:10:03,936
-He's shaped like a stingray.
-Isn't he?

255
00:10:04,003 --> 00:10:05,071
He's huge.

256
00:10:05,137 --> 00:10:06,472
What do you mean, a stingray?

257
00:10:06,539 --> 00:10:08,874
Doesn't it look like Kim Dong-hyun's back?

258
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:10,610
Or Don Lee.

259
00:10:10,676 --> 00:10:13,279
-That triangular shape isn't easy to get.
-How did he do that?

260
00:10:13,346 --> 00:10:14,947
How was that possible?

261
00:10:15,014 --> 00:10:17,183
Before I act,

262
00:10:17,249 --> 00:10:21,854
I'm the type
who gets physically ready first.

263
00:10:21,921 --> 00:10:23,823
When I imagined

264
00:10:23,889 --> 00:10:26,359
the most elite agent
in the National Intelligence Service,

265
00:10:26,425 --> 00:10:30,730
he wasn't someone nimble
and pretty-looking.

266
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:33,833
I thought I had to look bigger

267
00:10:33,899 --> 00:10:36,168
to play someone who could
knock out his enemy in one blow.

268
00:10:36,235 --> 00:10:39,505
So I worked out three hours a day

269
00:10:39,572 --> 00:10:42,041
and ate six meals.

270
00:10:42,108 --> 00:10:43,442
Six meals a day?

271
00:10:43,509 --> 00:10:48,280
My weight is usually around 67 kg,

272
00:10:48,347 --> 00:10:51,884
but I got up to 84 kg back then.

273
00:10:52,184 --> 00:10:53,586
WOW…

274
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,588
It's something like this.

275
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:57,423
After all, it's my job.

276
00:10:57,490 --> 00:11:02,094
So the process didn't feel exhausting
and I could push through with passion.

277
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:04,697
-It's his job, so…
-And this is our job.

278
00:11:05,931 --> 00:11:07,333
We have experts on gaining weight.

279
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,868
I've only been growing bigger.

280
00:11:08,934 --> 00:11:10,670
You can easily gain 10 kg.

281
00:11:10,736 --> 00:11:12,938
I find him amazing too.

282
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:16,542
As we age, our metabolism slows down.

283
00:11:16,609 --> 00:11:17,843
It's already happening to you?

284
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:19,145
You aren't 40 yet, are you?

285
00:11:19,211 --> 00:11:20,212
I'm 47.

286
00:11:20,279 --> 00:11:22,314
-Forty-seven?
-Really? Forty-seven?

287
00:11:22,381 --> 00:11:23,449
-Really?
-Yes.

288
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:24,583
-Really?
-And you're older?

289
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:26,385
I'm 49.

290
00:11:26,452 --> 00:11:27,987
-Were you born in 1978?
-Yes.

291
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,556
THE MEN IN THE SAME AGE SHAKE HANDS

292
00:11:30,623 --> 00:11:31,691
-You two are the same age?
-Yes.

293
00:11:31,757 --> 00:11:33,426
-Him and you, Poong?
-Yes.

294
00:11:33,492 --> 00:11:35,327
What happened to you?

295
00:11:35,394 --> 00:11:36,962
It's not my fault!

296
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:39,432
The world made me like this.

297
00:11:39,498 --> 00:11:42,001
-You should shed some weight too.
-Okay. I'll try.

298
00:11:42,068 --> 00:11:47,039
He's also known as a big romantic,

299
00:11:47,106 --> 00:11:50,409
and the video of his proposal
generated a lot of buzz.

300
00:11:50,476 --> 00:11:54,980
<i>There's something I want to ask you to do.</i>

301
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:56,148
<i>What is it? Tell me.</i>

302
00:11:59,218 --> 00:12:00,186
<i>What are you doing?</i>

303
00:12:02,154 --> 00:12:06,759
HIS SURPRISE PROPOSAL

304
00:12:12,932 --> 00:12:14,567
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

305
00:12:14,633 --> 00:12:15,801
IT'S LIKE A DRAMA… SHEESH…

306
00:12:15,868 --> 00:12:17,203
HE TURNED HIS PROPOSAL INTO A FILM

307
00:12:17,269 --> 00:12:18,571
SO BEAUTIFUL, TOUCHING, AND CINEMATIC

308
00:12:18,637 --> 00:12:22,875
Did you come up with the idea?

309
00:12:22,942 --> 00:12:26,746
I've watched countless
Hollywood films since I was young,

310
00:12:26,812 --> 00:12:31,517
so I always had the idea
that my proposal had to be like that.

311
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:35,321
Jung-hwan, when you proposed,
you gave her your bankbook?

312
00:12:35,387 --> 00:12:36,288
-Your bankbook?
-Bankbook?

313
00:12:36,355 --> 00:12:37,790
-I regret that.
-Why a bankbook?

314
00:12:37,857 --> 00:12:38,824
I regret it now.

315
00:12:38,891 --> 00:12:40,526
"I give you my everything!"

316
00:12:40,593 --> 00:12:41,994
I regret it so much.

317
00:12:42,061 --> 00:12:44,296
I should've saved up even more
before giving it to her.

318
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:47,366
That's my biggest regret.

319
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:49,268
CLAPPING

320
00:12:49,335 --> 00:12:51,904
Can you tell us how much you had?

321
00:12:51,971 --> 00:12:53,873
It was everything I saved up until then.

322
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:55,574
NICE JOB, MAN

323
00:12:55,641 --> 00:12:57,143
-You gave her 100% of it?
-Yes.

324
00:12:57,209 --> 00:12:58,844
-Whoa. That's amazing.
-Whoa.

325
00:12:58,911 --> 00:13:01,781
Hyun-suk would sulk if we didn't ask.

326
00:13:01,847 --> 00:13:03,449
I'm not sure if he'll remember.

327
00:13:03,516 --> 00:13:05,017
It happened a long time ago.

328
00:13:05,084 --> 00:13:06,852
-Maybe he gave her jade rings.
-No.

329
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:09,622
-A thin silver ring.
-Silver rings.

330
00:13:09,688 --> 00:13:12,358
Along with a <i>norigae</i>, a Korean pendant.

331
00:13:12,424 --> 00:13:13,959
You're going

332
00:13:14,026 --> 00:13:14,894
a bit overboard today.

333
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,028
TREMBLE

334
00:13:16,095 --> 00:13:17,396
-Enough is enough.
-Okay.

335
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:18,864
-You're walking on thin ice.
-Okay.

336
00:13:18,931 --> 00:13:20,432
Back in my day,

337
00:13:20,933 --> 00:13:22,501
proposals weren't a thing.

338
00:13:22,568 --> 00:13:24,703
Our parents would schedule
the wedding date,

339
00:13:24,770 --> 00:13:27,540
then we moved in and had kids.
That was life.

340
00:13:27,606 --> 00:13:29,375
-And become a grandpa.
-Proposal?

341
00:13:29,441 --> 00:13:31,510
Only someone who's got it good did that.

342
00:13:32,211 --> 00:13:34,847
It looks like Nam-no has an idea.

343
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:37,383
I'm not trying to be funny.
There's something I really want to do.

344
00:13:37,449 --> 00:13:38,717
-Noryangjin Fish Market?
-That again?

345
00:13:38,784 --> 00:13:40,519
-No.
-Majang-dong Meat Market?

346
00:13:40,586 --> 00:13:42,421
-How did you know?
-I knew it.

347
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:45,391
I want to go to a Korean beef
or a thin-sliced pork belly place.

348
00:13:45,457 --> 00:13:46,926
Right.

349
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:48,060
-I'm serious.
-Pork belly?

350
00:13:48,127 --> 00:13:50,362
-Some thin-sliced pork belly places…
-At a restaurant?

351
00:13:50,429 --> 00:13:53,365
…serve the meat in long pieces,
before they're chopped.

352
00:13:53,432 --> 00:13:55,301
I'll grill the meat

353
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:57,369
and use seasoned green onion
as the bouquet.

354
00:13:57,436 --> 00:13:59,004
And with the wedding ring,

355
00:13:59,071 --> 00:14:01,006
I'll put it in the <i>doenjang-jjigae</i>.

356
00:14:01,073 --> 00:14:03,642
-Inside the <i>doenjang-jjigae</i>?
-Yes.

357
00:14:03,709 --> 00:14:05,544
Do you want her to find it
while eating that?

358
00:14:05,611 --> 00:14:08,113
-It'll smell like <i>doenjang</i>.
-Yes.

359
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:09,782
You must rehearse everything in your head.

360
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:11,750
When she finds it inside,
she'll go, "Oh, my."

361
00:14:11,817 --> 00:14:12,885
And then, to wear it…

362
00:14:12,952 --> 00:14:13,953
LICKING OFF

363
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:16,121
-She'll have to do this.
-You're right.

364
00:14:16,422 --> 00:14:18,023
I LOVE IT ♥

365
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:21,026
Min seems to have a lot on his mind.
What do you think about that?

366
00:14:21,093 --> 00:14:22,995
-Isn't it novel?
-Well, the thing is,

367
00:14:23,062 --> 00:14:25,064
I could tell by the way he seemed
when he talked

368
00:14:25,130 --> 00:14:26,532
that he was serious.

369
00:14:27,132 --> 00:14:28,133
DEAD SERIOUS

370
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,335
I am dead serious.

371
00:14:29,401 --> 00:14:30,803
If he says so, he'll do it.

372
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,405
So I tried my best to understand.

373
00:14:33,472 --> 00:14:36,242
If his girlfriend at the time

374
00:14:36,308 --> 00:14:38,477
knows what he's like

375
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:42,314
and understands
he's doing this purely out of love,

376
00:14:42,381 --> 00:14:44,483
it would be very touching.

377
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:47,219
But most women would go,

378
00:14:47,286 --> 00:14:49,922
-"Is he kidding me?"
-It won't work.

379
00:14:49,989 --> 00:14:51,557
-Yes.
-Totally.

380
00:14:51,624 --> 00:14:54,059
He had already mentioned
that he wanted to have his wedding

381
00:14:54,126 --> 00:14:56,629
-at a fish restaurant and a meat place.
-You're right.

382
00:14:56,695 --> 00:14:58,664
I have to sing a wedding song
at a raw fish place?

383
00:14:59,231 --> 00:15:00,065
You want to do it again?

384
00:15:00,132 --> 00:15:01,734
I'm not having singers at my wedding.

385
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:04,503
Anyway, he's a born romantic.

386
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:07,606
We're now about to look
through Namkoong Min's fridge.

387
00:15:07,673 --> 00:15:09,942
I know that
you usually keep a strict diet.

388
00:15:10,009 --> 00:15:11,777
-Do you only have chicken breasts?
-Right?

389
00:15:11,844 --> 00:15:13,279
HAHAHA…

390
00:15:13,946 --> 00:15:15,481
-But he doesn't use it alone.
-No.

391
00:15:16,015 --> 00:15:18,350
HE USES IT WITH HIS WIFE

392
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:19,952
I'm only entitled to

393
00:15:20,019 --> 00:15:23,555
about 5% of what's in there.

394
00:15:23,622 --> 00:15:26,859
-So 95% of it is my wife's.
-I see.

395
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:27,760
We'll be okay, then.

396
00:15:27,826 --> 00:15:30,529
-He doesn't use it alone. Okay.
-Exactly.

397
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:33,999
-We present Min's fridge!
-Fridge!

398
00:15:34,066 --> 00:15:34,934
-Whoa.
-Hey.

399
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,101
-Wow.
-Yes.

400
00:15:36,168 --> 00:15:37,002
That's a lot.

401
00:15:37,636 --> 00:15:39,972
PRESENTING NAMKOONG MIN'S FRIDGE

402
00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:40,940
It looks neat.

403
00:15:41,006 --> 00:15:43,475
Everything looks neatly organized.

404
00:15:43,542 --> 00:15:45,611
HA HA HA HA!

405
00:15:45,678 --> 00:15:47,346
It's labeled.

406
00:15:47,413 --> 00:15:50,950
"Roasted perilla powder.
Good until January 20th, 2027."

407
00:15:51,216 --> 00:15:52,318
AMAZED

408
00:15:53,085 --> 00:15:56,488
Is this how the fridge always is?
Or did your wife pay extra attention?

409
00:15:56,555 --> 00:15:58,190
I think she put in

410
00:15:58,257 --> 00:16:00,559
-about 3% more effort.
-She probably needed that 3%.

411
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:02,995
-Three percent.
-After all, it'll be aired.

412
00:16:03,062 --> 00:16:06,198
I see some vegetables up here.

413
00:16:06,265 --> 00:16:09,535
-I think that's melon.
-Yes, it looks like melon.

414
00:16:09,601 --> 00:16:10,903
-Cherry tomatoes.
-Yes.

415
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:13,105
-Chopped cucumber.
-Yes.

416
00:16:13,172 --> 00:16:15,140
-Because her husband is on a diet.
-What's that?

417
00:16:15,207 --> 00:16:16,675
Next, this one.

418
00:16:16,742 --> 00:16:18,243
-Sausage and veggies?
-Broccoli and tomatoes.

419
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:19,411
OH… BROCCOLI AND TOMATOES…

420
00:16:19,478 --> 00:16:21,113
-How healthy.
-I hate it.

421
00:16:21,180 --> 00:16:22,915
I see something chunky.

422
00:16:23,816 --> 00:16:24,817
Hey.

423
00:16:24,883 --> 00:16:27,619
-I eat those as a snack.
-<i>Tteokgalbi</i>?

424
00:16:27,686 --> 00:16:28,520
Mushroom and…

425
00:16:28,587 --> 00:16:31,190
-Do you eat this as is?
-Yes.

426
00:16:31,256 --> 00:16:34,259
-Does she pack these for you?
-Yes.

427
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:36,228
These look very dry.

428
00:16:36,295 --> 00:16:38,130
You know what? Even so,

429
00:16:38,197 --> 00:16:41,533
I am not allowed to say that
or make those faces.

430
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,268
"Can I have some sauce with it?"

431
00:16:43,335 --> 00:16:45,537
-"Can I at least have some sauce, honey?"
-No.

432
00:16:45,604 --> 00:16:47,740
-No? Whatever she packs?
-I can't do that.

433
00:16:47,806 --> 00:16:48,640
I'll get in trouble.

434
00:16:48,707 --> 00:16:50,642
-Just eat it not to get in trouble.
-He's on a diet.

435
00:16:50,709 --> 00:16:52,878
The one on the right
is probably a mix of everything.

436
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:55,414
PREPPED INGREDIENTS, ACTUAL MEAL

437
00:16:55,481 --> 00:16:56,949
Here's his actual meal.

438
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:59,485
With cheese and all.

439
00:16:59,551 --> 00:17:00,686
-Meat.
-Salmon.

440
00:17:00,753 --> 00:17:05,224
She puts that in a cooler bag
with ice packs for me

441
00:17:05,290 --> 00:17:06,959
-in the morning.
-Even a cooler bag?

442
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:08,127
How sweet of her.

443
00:17:08,193 --> 00:17:10,129
Even ice packs. She's so considerate.

444
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:12,931
-So this is your lunch?
-Yes.

445
00:17:12,998 --> 00:17:18,137
I'm the type who looks bloated
the moment I eat even a little.

446
00:17:18,203 --> 00:17:20,672
So I tend to eat it
after I finish an important scene.

447
00:17:20,739 --> 00:17:23,609
But that kind of food
can never make you look bloated.

448
00:17:23,675 --> 00:17:27,346
YOU LOOK BLOATED AFTER EATING THIS?

449
00:17:27,413 --> 00:17:29,048
-Can you show us?
-Sure.

450
00:17:29,114 --> 00:17:32,451
Can our backs look like yours
if we eat like that too?

451
00:17:32,518 --> 00:17:34,153
If you want to eat like that,

452
00:17:34,219 --> 00:17:36,488
-you'll have to eat eight boxes of those.
-Really?

453
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:39,758
-Is this Chinese yam?
-Yes, I have it as a drink.

454
00:17:39,825 --> 00:17:41,693
Before I leave in the morning,

455
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:44,997
she blends Chinese yam, banana,

456
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:49,101
and bean flour to make me a drink.

457
00:17:49,168 --> 00:17:51,070
At times, I'd drink it

458
00:17:51,136 --> 00:17:52,938
and feel a bit iffy inside.

459
00:17:53,005 --> 00:17:55,874
-It does feel kind of odd.
-Does it make you gassy?

460
00:17:55,941 --> 00:17:58,310
But still, I enjoy it very much.

461
00:17:58,377 --> 00:18:00,079
So very much.

462
00:18:00,145 --> 00:18:01,780
When she makes that for me,

463
00:18:01,847 --> 00:18:03,215
I chug it right away.

464
00:18:03,282 --> 00:18:05,317
You seem to be extremely formal with her.

465
00:18:05,384 --> 00:18:08,220
Yes, right? Why am I doing that?

466
00:18:08,287 --> 00:18:10,856
-Original flavor.
-Chicken breasts.

467
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:12,825
You've already had a lot.

468
00:18:12,891 --> 00:18:15,527
That's the only share I have
in this fridge.

469
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:17,663
When my wife isn't around,

470
00:18:17,729 --> 00:18:21,266
I warm that and instant rice
and make do with it.

471
00:18:22,034 --> 00:18:23,268
Only when she isn't around.

472
00:18:23,335 --> 00:18:25,204
When I have a shoot the next day,

473
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:28,307
I don't really consider the taste
when I eat. I just eat.

474
00:18:28,373 --> 00:18:29,842
What if you don't have a shoot?

475
00:18:29,908 --> 00:18:32,478
I start binging like crazy,
ordering hamburgers and such.

476
00:18:32,544 --> 00:18:34,880
-Start with a burger.
-So you do like to eat.

477
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:37,683
How does he control himself?
If I crave a burger, I have to eat it.

478
00:18:37,749 --> 00:18:42,387
What's something that you love
but stay away from to keep your shape?

479
00:18:42,454 --> 00:18:46,091
I like to eat something that I call
the food that makes you uglier.

480
00:18:46,158 --> 00:18:48,660
-Food that makes you uglier?
-Food that makes you uglier? What's that?

481
00:18:48,727 --> 00:18:51,063
-What's that?
-The kind of food

482
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:53,065
that makes your blood sugar spike.

483
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,100
-What Poong makes.
-Pizza.

484
00:18:55,167 --> 00:18:56,902
-Pork belly. Also…
-Pork belly.

485
00:18:56,969 --> 00:18:58,704
…<i>tteokbokki</i>.

486
00:18:58,770 --> 00:19:00,239
<i>Jjajangmyeon</i>.

487
00:19:00,305 --> 00:19:02,808
I love everything like that.

488
00:19:02,875 --> 00:19:05,144
Do you also become uglier
when you eat that kind of food?

489
00:19:05,210 --> 00:19:06,912
-It's…
-How do you look afterward?

490
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,313
THIS FACE CAN GET UGLIER?

491
00:19:08,380 --> 00:19:10,282
You'll see some examples right there.

492
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:11,550
EXAMPLES OF UGLIER

493
00:19:11,617 --> 00:19:14,019
-I believe they eat quite a lot.
-<i>Tteokbokki</i>, pork belly.

494
00:19:14,086 --> 00:19:16,622
-They love food that makes them uglier.
-They're in great shape.

495
00:19:18,123 --> 00:19:19,224
It costs me a lot.

496
00:19:19,291 --> 00:19:20,626
It's expensive to keep up this shape.

497
00:19:20,692 --> 00:19:22,794
-A luxurious body.
-Really.

498
00:19:22,861 --> 00:19:25,664
If I eat like that for just two days,

499
00:19:25,731 --> 00:19:30,302
-I immediately gain 3 kg. In 2 days.
-In just 2 days?

500
00:19:30,369 --> 00:19:33,038
Can you relate? Do you
also feel uglier when you eat these?

501
00:19:33,105 --> 00:19:36,208
It's actually not so bad
if you eat just pork belly.

502
00:19:36,275 --> 00:19:39,344
The problem is that you want to finish
with <i>bibim-naengmyeon.</i>

503
00:19:39,411 --> 00:19:41,747
The moment I eat
a bowl of that to end the meal,

504
00:19:41,813 --> 00:19:45,717
my face becomes so big
that you'll wonder if I'd been beaten.

505
00:19:45,784 --> 00:19:48,687
The more the food ruins your face,
the more delicious it is.

506
00:19:48,754 --> 00:19:50,455
-Correct.
-You're right.

507
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:52,191
You must eat delicious food every day.

508
00:19:52,491 --> 00:19:53,659
HEHE ♥

509
00:19:53,725 --> 00:19:55,694
-He means you're ugly.
-As we speak,

510
00:19:55,761 --> 00:19:58,697
-I found whelk. Do you eat whelk?
-Whelkie, whelkie.

511
00:19:58,764 --> 00:20:02,134
It's been a while since I had bought that.

512
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:05,137
When I crave a drink,

513
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,773
I buy just a can of beer
and a can of whelk.

514
00:20:07,839 --> 00:20:10,576
Then, I put the beer in the freezer
the moment I come home,

515
00:20:10,642 --> 00:20:13,645
shower, come out, put on
skin care products, and pull it out.

516
00:20:13,712 --> 00:20:17,316
-Then it's perfectly chilled.
-It must be insanely good.

517
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:19,851
I don't want to chug it too quickly,

518
00:20:19,918 --> 00:20:24,656
so at times, I use a straw and sip on it

519
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:25,791
very slowly.

520
00:20:25,857 --> 00:20:27,559
That'll last you a while,

521
00:20:27,626 --> 00:20:29,962
for about ten minutes or so.

522
00:20:30,028 --> 00:20:33,198
-So these whelk is your bar snack.
-That's right.

523
00:20:33,265 --> 00:20:36,468
I bought that can of whelk with a beer,

524
00:20:36,535 --> 00:20:40,239
and I haven't had a drink until now.

525
00:20:40,305 --> 00:20:41,907
I see some alcoholic drinks here.

526
00:20:41,974 --> 00:20:44,743
Wait, this is nonalcoholic beer?

527
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:47,145
If you drink half a can very fast,

528
00:20:47,212 --> 00:20:50,182
it feels like the real deal.

529
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:52,484
-Quickly. That's the key.
-That's how I quench my cravings.

530
00:20:52,551 --> 00:20:54,987
-That's how you control yourself.
-I see.

531
00:20:55,053 --> 00:20:56,521
Like a sandwich without meat.

532
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:58,257
Like a bun without red bean.

533
00:20:58,323 --> 00:21:01,560
-You only have one can of actual beer.
-It's because

534
00:21:01,627 --> 00:21:03,662
the moment I have one beer,

535
00:21:03,729 --> 00:21:05,430
I just can't stop.

536
00:21:05,497 --> 00:21:06,932
He can't control himself.

537
00:21:06,999 --> 00:21:09,268
That's why I only get one beer.

538
00:21:09,334 --> 00:21:12,137
You'll keep thinking about
the rest of the beer in the fridge.

539
00:21:12,204 --> 00:21:14,306
-Don't you?
-Yes, I do!

540
00:21:14,373 --> 00:21:16,441
I can even visualize where it is.

541
00:21:16,508 --> 00:21:18,110
"Should I have one more?"

542
00:21:18,176 --> 00:21:21,446
-I get it.
-What if you don't have to stay in shape?

543
00:21:21,513 --> 00:21:24,383
-Do you let yourself go?
-When I don't have to,

544
00:21:24,449 --> 00:21:26,451
first, I make plans
to meet with my friends.

545
00:21:26,518 --> 00:21:30,188
We usually meet up around 6 p.m. to 7 p.m.

546
00:21:30,255 --> 00:21:32,491
Then we go hard from the start

547
00:21:32,557 --> 00:21:34,960
until around 4 or 5 a.m.

548
00:21:35,027 --> 00:21:39,731
I once drank for 14 hours straight.

549
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:41,333
-Whoa.
-14 hours?

550
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,336
-You can probably tolerate a lot.
-I'm sure he can hold it.

551
00:21:44,403 --> 00:21:46,505
If I switch between the types of alcohol,

552
00:21:46,571 --> 00:21:47,939
I can pretty much keep going.

553
00:21:48,006 --> 00:21:49,775
-Doesn't that get you more drunk?
-I see.

554
00:21:49,841 --> 00:21:52,978
-Right? I don't think I can do that.
-Here's the thing with me.

555
00:21:53,045 --> 00:21:56,682
When I go somewhere,
I first crave a draft beer,

556
00:21:56,748 --> 00:21:59,985
then a glass of champagne or white wine.

557
00:22:00,052 --> 00:22:01,887
After that, I'll want some red wine,

558
00:22:01,953 --> 00:22:04,056
and then a highball.

559
00:22:04,122 --> 00:22:05,891
Once we've gotten pretty far in,

560
00:22:05,957 --> 00:22:09,161
I end the night
with some <i>somaek</i>, soju and beer,

561
00:22:09,227 --> 00:22:11,463
along with some pork belly.

562
00:22:11,530 --> 00:22:15,067
The amount he has on that shelf
is what he can drink in a day.

563
00:22:15,133 --> 00:22:16,635
-Six hours' worth.
-It's just as you said.

564
00:22:17,135 --> 00:22:19,705
MANY DIFFERENT ALCOHOLIC DRINKS
THAT REFLECTS HIS TASTE

565
00:22:19,771 --> 00:22:22,274
But at times,
you sit in regret after drinking?

566
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:23,909
When I drink a lot,

567
00:22:23,975 --> 00:22:26,745
my long-suppressed appetite unleashes,

568
00:22:26,812 --> 00:22:30,382
and I eat those dishes,
the food that makes you uglier.

569
00:22:30,449 --> 00:22:32,084
-That makes you uglier.
-In a way,

570
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:34,720
-He keeps looking at us.
-…it must be the kind of food

571
00:22:34,786 --> 00:22:37,656
that I instinctively think is delicious,

572
00:22:37,723 --> 00:22:40,225
-<i>Jjajangmyeon</i> or <i>tteokbokki…</i>
-You crave carbs.

573
00:22:40,292 --> 00:22:43,161
suddenly sit on top of my table

574
00:22:43,228 --> 00:22:45,263
without me realizing it.

575
00:22:45,330 --> 00:22:48,133
-He must order delivery food.
-Or <i>ramyeon.</i> Something like that.

576
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:49,701
Recently, when I came home,

577
00:22:49,768 --> 00:22:51,870
I saw a bunch of <i>dureup,</i>

578
00:22:51,937 --> 00:22:55,006
and I dipped it in gochujang
and finished everything.

579
00:22:55,073 --> 00:22:56,208
It wasn't even cooked.

580
00:22:56,274 --> 00:22:58,977
You feel famished when you're drunk.

581
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:00,946
It must've been fun

582
00:23:01,012 --> 00:23:02,647
for me to eat those <i>dureup</i>.

583
00:23:02,714 --> 00:23:06,952
So after I finished those, I made <i>ramyeon</i>
and added some rice to it too.

584
00:23:07,018 --> 00:23:08,487
I regretted it later

585
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:10,722
-but I was really happy that day.
-I see.

586
00:23:10,789 --> 00:23:13,558
He isn't someone who only eats healthy.

587
00:23:13,625 --> 00:23:15,794
-Of course not.
-He has great self-control.

588
00:23:15,861 --> 00:23:17,662
Now, the freezer.

589
00:23:17,729 --> 00:23:20,766
Scallops and many other seafood.

590
00:23:20,832 --> 00:23:22,567
Clams. Abalones.

591
00:23:22,634 --> 00:23:23,668
Do you enjoy seafood?

592
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:27,205
I love it. I love seafood dishes.

593
00:23:27,272 --> 00:23:29,341
Right underneath is some meat.

594
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:31,042
He has both pork and beef.

595
00:23:31,109 --> 00:23:32,444
Which do you prefer?

596
00:23:32,511 --> 00:23:35,380
I think I like pork better.

597
00:23:35,947 --> 00:23:39,851
I mostly ate beef tenderloin
while I was filming <i>The Veil,</i>

598
00:23:39,918 --> 00:23:44,589
but seeing that I choose to eat pork
when I get drunk, it must be pork.

599
00:23:44,656 --> 00:23:48,260
He's very disciplined,
so he keeps gaslighting himself.

600
00:23:48,326 --> 00:23:51,062
I can't find a moment
to chime in on the conversation today.

601
00:23:51,129 --> 00:23:52,464
-May we make you happy today?
-Yes.

602
00:23:52,531 --> 00:23:54,132
I don't want to care

603
00:23:54,199 --> 00:23:56,668
about putting on weight today.

604
00:23:56,735 --> 00:23:58,770
I just want to pursue my happiness.

605
00:23:59,771 --> 00:24:01,106
YAY FOR NAM-NO

606
00:24:01,173 --> 00:24:03,008
That's all for his fridge!

607
00:24:03,074 --> 00:24:04,876
FINISHED CHECKING OUT MIN'S FRIDGE

608
00:24:04,943 --> 00:24:09,281
I wonder what he's looking to eat today.

609
00:24:09,347 --> 00:24:11,316
What are his orders?

610
00:24:11,383 --> 00:24:14,286
What's the first one? The Somaek.

611
00:24:14,352 --> 00:24:16,121
-The Somaek.
-You came ready to drink.

612
00:24:16,188 --> 00:24:18,390
Toward the end of my drinking night,

613
00:24:18,457 --> 00:24:21,726
I mostly finish with <i>somaek</i>,
a mix of soju and beer.

614
00:24:21,793 --> 00:24:24,262
So I want to ask you
to make me a bar snack

615
00:24:24,329 --> 00:24:27,432
that'll go well with <i>somaek</i>.

616
00:24:27,499 --> 00:24:29,968
I see. This is toward
the end of the night.

617
00:24:30,035 --> 00:24:32,170
-The bar snack that'll be the finale.
-The finale.

618
00:24:32,237 --> 00:24:34,406
What's the second order?

619
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:38,710
-What's the second one? The Ugliness.
-The Ugliness.

620
00:24:38,777 --> 00:24:40,445
-What's this?
-I can't do that one.

621
00:24:40,512 --> 00:24:44,149
I always eat things like
vegetables or chicken breasts,

622
00:24:44,216 --> 00:24:46,785
something I deluded myself
into thinking that I like.

623
00:24:46,852 --> 00:24:47,919
Instead of those…

624
00:24:47,986 --> 00:24:51,022
I don't care how it changes my looks.

625
00:24:51,089 --> 00:24:55,126
I want to eat something
that's purely and instinctively delicious.

626
00:24:55,193 --> 00:24:58,029
-Please make me something like that.
-Okay.

627
00:24:58,096 --> 00:25:00,365
Now, The Somaek and The Ugliness.

628
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:04,236
-And their drama is? <i>The Husband.</i>
<i>-The Husband.</i>

629
00:25:04,302 --> 00:25:09,107
Let's give the first chance
to Chef Moon-jung.

630
00:25:09,174 --> 00:25:13,044
I'll go with The Somaek.

631
00:25:13,111 --> 00:25:15,080
-The Somaek.
-She loves a good drink.

632
00:25:15,146 --> 00:25:17,582
-I can't take it well, but I enjoy it.
-But she can.

633
00:25:17,649 --> 00:25:19,284
Then today,

634
00:25:19,351 --> 00:25:20,986
who would you like to fight?

635
00:25:21,052 --> 00:25:22,087
WHO WILL SHE TAKE DOWN?

636
00:25:22,153 --> 00:25:25,190
-Anyone you want to compete against?
-Someone you want to beat.

637
00:25:25,257 --> 00:25:27,325
Someone you want to defeat
before you go on.

638
00:25:27,392 --> 00:25:28,994
The one sitting right across from me,

639
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:31,162
-Kim Poong.
-I knew it.

640
00:25:31,229 --> 00:25:33,331
-I'll fight him.
-It was about time.

641
00:25:33,398 --> 00:25:38,270
Some say <i>CCW</i> is pretty much known as
the Road to Kim Poong.

642
00:25:38,336 --> 00:25:40,572
It doesn't matter if you win on <i>CCW</i>,

643
00:25:40,639 --> 00:25:42,307
because you'll come here and face Poong.

644
00:25:42,374 --> 00:25:43,708
That is preposterous.

645
00:25:44,276 --> 00:25:46,978
I'll think of this as my last chance

646
00:25:47,045 --> 00:25:48,747
-to take him down today.
-I see.

647
00:25:48,813 --> 00:25:50,882
-It won't be an easy day.
-How scary.

648
00:25:50,949 --> 00:25:53,184
Well, I am the gatekeeper of the show.

649
00:25:53,385 --> 00:25:54,519
THE GATEKEEPER?

650
00:25:54,586 --> 00:25:56,054
-The goalie.
-Yes.

651
00:25:56,121 --> 00:25:58,056
As <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>'s gatekeeper,

652
00:25:58,123 --> 00:26:00,025
I'll show her how difficult it is

653
00:26:00,091 --> 00:26:02,360
just to get her feet in this studio.

654
00:26:02,427 --> 00:26:05,297
-Are you in?
-I'll join The Somaek.

655
00:26:05,363 --> 00:26:08,333
Poong accepts her challenge.

656
00:26:08,567 --> 00:26:11,002
THE ROAD TO KIM POONG HAS BEEN SET UP

657
00:26:11,069 --> 00:26:13,972
The next order is The Ugliness.

658
00:26:14,039 --> 00:26:15,140
I'll join.

659
00:26:15,340 --> 00:26:16,775
SURPRISED

660
00:26:16,841 --> 00:26:18,743
You startled me.

661
00:26:18,810 --> 00:26:20,745
But that guy has

662
00:26:20,812 --> 00:26:22,614
already fulfilled that order.

663
00:26:23,548 --> 00:26:25,317
PERFECT LOOKS FOR IT

664
00:26:25,383 --> 00:26:27,152
-His hand shot up.
-He's adorable.

665
00:26:27,218 --> 00:26:28,053
Sure, he's cute.

666
00:26:28,119 --> 00:26:30,355
-But under one condition.
-There's a condition?

667
00:26:30,422 --> 00:26:32,857
I'd like to take Ugly Two with me.

668
00:26:33,124 --> 00:26:34,192
DRAGGING HIM IN

669
00:26:34,259 --> 00:26:37,329
-He doesn't seem to think so.
-Sung-jun doesn't think so.

670
00:26:37,395 --> 00:26:38,830
He's not thinking that at all.

671
00:26:38,897 --> 00:26:41,433
Okay, but I'm not joining the round
because I'm bad-looking.

672
00:26:41,499 --> 00:26:43,602
I like the idea of that order,

673
00:26:43,668 --> 00:26:45,937
and he has the least number of stars.

674
00:26:46,004 --> 00:26:47,539
He should be coming here to cook,

675
00:26:47,606 --> 00:26:49,207
but he comes to eat. That's why.

676
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:50,875
CAN'T ARGUE

677
00:26:50,942 --> 00:26:53,445
-Nam-no drags him in.
-Let's settle this today.

678
00:26:53,511 --> 00:26:57,482
All right.
Both cook-offs have been decided.

679
00:26:57,549 --> 00:26:59,884
First, The Somaek.

680
00:26:59,951 --> 00:27:03,521
Let us begin the cook-off
between Moon-jung and Poong!

681
00:27:04,422 --> 00:27:06,591
THE SOMAEK BAR SNACK ROUND BEGINS NOW

682
00:27:06,658 --> 00:27:11,029
<i>This is the first cook-off,</i>
<i>played with ingredients from Min's fridge.</i>

683
00:27:11,596 --> 00:27:14,165
First, she took down Eun-yeong,
and now, she's here for Poong.

684
00:27:14,232 --> 00:27:16,835
Witch With a Wok, Chef Yi Moon-jung,

685
00:27:17,402 --> 00:27:20,338
versus the gatekeeper of darkness
who's here to stop the witch,

686
00:27:20,405 --> 00:27:22,974
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

687
00:27:23,041 --> 00:27:25,176
He said something like this.

688
00:27:25,243 --> 00:27:28,480
"Today is the day
the Witch will cry a river."

689
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:29,981
ADMITS COMPLETELY

690
00:27:30,048 --> 00:27:32,951
-You're currently in second place.
-I am.

691
00:27:33,184 --> 00:27:34,519
WHO WOULD'VE THOUGHT?

692
00:27:34,586 --> 00:27:36,554
-As second place…
-When did things start to go haywire?

693
00:27:36,621 --> 00:27:39,157
Who was that one person again?

694
00:27:39,224 --> 00:27:40,125
Little Tiger?

695
00:27:40,191 --> 00:27:41,493
Yes, Little Tiger. Right.

696
00:27:41,559 --> 00:27:43,662
Little Tiger made a quick visit, then…

697
00:27:44,462 --> 00:27:48,033
THE GATEKEEPER'S RAMPAGE

698
00:27:48,466 --> 00:27:50,869
DEFEATED LITTLE TIGER IN THE END

699
00:27:50,935 --> 00:27:52,771
She came with a "rawr,"

700
00:27:52,837 --> 00:27:54,606
but she left with tears in her eyes.

701
00:27:54,673 --> 00:27:56,374
-You're right.
-Yes.

702
00:27:56,441 --> 00:27:58,710
The thing is, you must beat me

703
00:27:58,777 --> 00:28:01,680
before you challenge
other chefs of the show.

704
00:28:01,746 --> 00:28:03,014
So let me stop her

705
00:28:03,081 --> 00:28:05,784
from even making it past the gate.

706
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:08,486
Starting with the one he mentioned,
Little Tiger,

707
00:28:08,553 --> 00:28:12,557
he has been devouring the chefs
one after another.

708
00:28:12,624 --> 00:28:13,892
-He ate us up.
-So today,

709
00:28:13,958 --> 00:28:16,127
I will prey on

710
00:28:16,194 --> 00:28:18,897
Kim Poong and end him.

711
00:28:19,964 --> 00:28:22,434
-Her words are so charismatic.
-I'm scared.

712
00:28:22,500 --> 00:28:25,303
The order is something
very advantageous for Poong,

713
00:28:25,370 --> 00:28:26,538
The Somaek.

714
00:28:26,604 --> 00:28:29,074
When it comes to a round
that involves an alcoholic drink,

715
00:28:29,140 --> 00:28:31,710
-you have an exceptionally high win rate.
-You're correct.

716
00:28:31,776 --> 00:28:34,979
Are you sure you can beat him
with a bar snack for <i>somaek</i>?

717
00:28:35,580 --> 00:28:36,715
Actually, I am

718
00:28:36,781 --> 00:28:38,917
the Witch of <i>Somaek</i>.

719
00:28:38,983 --> 00:28:42,654
-Witch of <i>Somaek</i>?
-Witch of <i>Somaek</i>? We haven't heard that.

720
00:28:42,721 --> 00:28:44,689
I have spent

721
00:28:44,756 --> 00:28:46,725
twenty-five years to be here now.

722
00:28:46,791 --> 00:28:49,060
AND SHE HAS DRUNK THAT MUCH SOMAEK

723
00:28:49,127 --> 00:28:54,199
I'll gladly display
the power of <i>somaek </i>today.

724
00:28:55,133 --> 00:28:57,135
WEBTOON ARTIST POONG'S INGREDIENTS:
MACKEREL, CURRY BLOCK, AVOCADO

725
00:28:57,202 --> 00:28:59,204
TOMATO, RED CHILI PEPPER,
SPICY BIBIM-JANG, TUNA SAUCE, AND MORE

726
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:01,172
What are you making, Poong?

727
00:29:01,239 --> 00:29:03,742
The name of my dish is

728
00:29:03,808 --> 00:29:07,746
Mackerel Will Make You Chug Somaek!

729
00:29:07,812 --> 00:29:09,581
CREDIT WHERE CREDIT'S DUE

730
00:29:09,647 --> 00:29:11,616
-I've heard that tone before.
-That's it.

731
00:29:11,683 --> 00:29:13,118
What I'm going to make

732
00:29:13,184 --> 00:29:15,019
is something that's viral right now.

733
00:29:15,086 --> 00:29:16,588
Have you heard of an onion wrap?

734
00:29:16,654 --> 00:29:18,189
-Onion wrap?
-Yes.

735
00:29:18,256 --> 00:29:20,158
FOODIE NAM-NO KNOWS

736
00:29:20,225 --> 00:29:22,560
You take spicy fire <i>ramyeon</i>
or whatever else you have

737
00:29:22,627 --> 00:29:24,195
and wrap it with raw onion.

738
00:29:24,262 --> 00:29:25,497
-Like lettuce.
-Originally,

739
00:29:25,563 --> 00:29:28,600
in the southern region,
they eat pike eel shabu-shabu

740
00:29:28,666 --> 00:29:31,336
exactly like that, with raw onion.

741
00:29:31,402 --> 00:29:36,541
So the younger generation picked it up
and it's pretty popular now.

742
00:29:36,608 --> 00:29:38,443
-I'll do it with mackerel.
-Mackerel?

743
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:41,212
-I'll deep-fry mackerel.
-I see.

744
00:29:41,279 --> 00:29:46,251
So you'll eat onion wraps
with pieces of deep-fried mackerel.

745
00:29:46,317 --> 00:29:50,088
On the inside,
I'll add my special cream sauce.

746
00:29:50,155 --> 00:29:52,290
With that sauce, you can enjoy

747
00:29:52,357 --> 00:29:53,691
-the wraps in one bite.
-Sounds good.

748
00:29:53,758 --> 00:29:55,426
GULP

749
00:29:56,361 --> 00:29:58,363
CHEF MOON-JUNG'S INGREDIENTS:
CHINESE YAM, CANNED WHELK, SHRIMP

750
00:29:58,429 --> 00:30:00,431
CUCUMBER, APPLE, TOMATO,
BIBIMMYEON, RED CHILI PEPPER, AND MORE

751
00:30:00,498 --> 00:30:03,535
Chef Yi Moon-jung is up against him.
What are you going to make?

752
00:30:03,601 --> 00:30:05,937
The dish I'm making today

753
00:30:06,004 --> 00:30:07,605
will be magically enchanting.

754
00:30:07,672 --> 00:30:08,840
Magically enchanting.

755
00:30:08,907 --> 00:30:12,110
It'll help you drink endlessly
with this spell.

756
00:30:12,177 --> 00:30:15,480
It's called
Abracadabooze, AlakaChineseYam.

757
00:30:15,547 --> 00:30:18,049
I see. Abracadabooze, AlakaChineseYam.

758
00:30:18,249 --> 00:30:19,384
SHAKING HEAD

759
00:30:19,450 --> 00:30:23,988
After hearing that
Min eats Chinese yam every day,

760
00:30:24,055 --> 00:30:26,591
I decided to grind this

761
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:28,893
and use it as frying batter

762
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:31,329
for crunchy yet juicy fritters.

763
00:30:31,396 --> 00:30:33,264
It'll make you feel something
you've never felt before.

764
00:30:34,766 --> 00:30:37,402
"Is this a fritter or a whelk?"

765
00:30:37,468 --> 00:30:39,537
You'll be left wondering.

766
00:30:39,604 --> 00:30:41,973
I'll use whelks
and the Chinese sweet and spicy sauce

767
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:44,042
-Sweet and spicy.
-to make sweet and spicy fried whelk.

768
00:30:44,108 --> 00:30:47,478
I've prepared another magic

769
00:30:47,545 --> 00:30:48,880
you can enjoy with your eyes first

770
00:30:48,947 --> 00:30:50,548
even before tasting it.

771
00:30:50,615 --> 00:30:54,519
I want your road ahead
to be filled with flowers and sunshine,

772
00:30:54,586 --> 00:30:57,021
so I'll serve it with the Witch Flower.

773
00:30:57,088 --> 00:30:58,489
-Witch Flower?
-Witch Flower?

774
00:30:58,556 --> 00:31:00,825
-Flower?
-Look forward to it.

775
00:31:00,892 --> 00:31:04,329
Min will easily chug on drinks,

776
00:31:04,395 --> 00:31:07,332
I'll easily take Poong down

777
00:31:07,398 --> 00:31:10,802
and easily win a star with my spell.

778
00:31:11,736 --> 00:31:14,172
A ROUND OF APPLAUSE

779
00:31:14,239 --> 00:31:15,440
She's so good with words.

780
00:31:15,506 --> 00:31:16,908
That was like a play.

781
00:31:16,975 --> 00:31:19,611
-Like a <i>pansori </i>performance.
-<i>Pansori</i>.

782
00:31:19,677 --> 00:31:21,613
You sound like
you've been with us for months.

783
00:31:21,679 --> 00:31:25,083
-Her eyes are the same as Eun-yeong's.
-All right.

784
00:31:25,149 --> 00:31:30,255
And now, let us begin
the cook-off titled The Somaek.

785
00:31:31,222 --> 00:31:32,257
Wow.

786
00:31:32,824 --> 00:31:37,161
He has brought Little Tiger to tears,
and he will do it to Witch With a Wok.

787
00:31:37,228 --> 00:31:40,431
The gatekeeper of <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

788
00:31:40,498 --> 00:31:42,400
This is so chaotic.

789
00:31:42,467 --> 00:31:44,669
She's here to defeat Poong with her magic,

790
00:31:44,736 --> 00:31:48,139
because he now seems to think he's a chef.

791
00:31:48,206 --> 00:31:50,675
Witch With a Wok, Chef Yi Moon-jung is up!

792
00:31:50,742 --> 00:31:52,310
The Road to Kim Poong!

793
00:31:52,377 --> 00:31:54,245
Who will rise as the winner?

794
00:31:54,312 --> 00:31:57,916
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

795
00:31:59,317 --> 00:32:01,386
You'll be making bar snacks for <i>somaek</i>.

796
00:32:01,819 --> 00:32:04,155
THE WITCH VERSUS THE COOK OF THE DARKNESS

797
00:32:05,390 --> 00:32:07,492
SHINK, SHINK

798
00:32:07,558 --> 00:32:09,560
SEIZES THE UPPER HAND
BY SHARPENING THE KNIFE

799
00:32:09,627 --> 00:32:11,596
Yi Moon-jung with double swords.

800
00:32:12,063 --> 00:32:13,364
NOW… LET ME BEGIN

801
00:32:14,132 --> 00:32:16,834
It's happening in real-time. Wow.

802
00:32:16,901 --> 00:32:20,571
Moon-jung starts by prepping Chinese yam.

803
00:32:20,638 --> 00:32:22,173
She's really quick.

804
00:32:22,607 --> 00:32:23,675
LAYS OUT PARCHMENT PAPER

805
00:32:23,741 --> 00:32:25,677
She's grinding the yam!

806
00:32:25,743 --> 00:32:27,445
-She's slicing it.
-She's slicing.

807
00:32:27,512 --> 00:32:29,347
-She's not grinding it.
-Into slices.

808
00:32:29,414 --> 00:32:31,416
She's turning the yam into slices.

809
00:32:31,482 --> 00:32:34,352
-You're right. They're like potato chips.
-And she's grinding some too.

810
00:32:34,419 --> 00:32:36,287
She's grinding the rest.

811
00:32:36,354 --> 00:32:39,057
-She's slicing and grinding it.
-That's what happens?

812
00:32:39,123 --> 00:32:41,559
-It looks thick.
-That's Chinese yam.

813
00:32:41,626 --> 00:32:43,361
Poong grabs an onion first

814
00:32:43,428 --> 00:32:45,330
to make Gen Z's favorite dish.

815
00:32:45,396 --> 00:32:48,066
Sung-jun, do younger people
really like onion wrap?

816
00:32:48,132 --> 00:32:50,401
I've never heard of it.

817
00:32:50,468 --> 00:32:51,836
It's the most viral recipe.

818
00:32:51,903 --> 00:32:54,639
People often make a wrap
with pork belly and everything else

819
00:32:54,706 --> 00:32:56,040
with a piece of onion.

820
00:32:56,107 --> 00:32:58,443
-Instead of lettuce.
-Instead of lettuce?

821
00:32:58,509 --> 00:33:00,144
It tastes refreshing.

822
00:33:00,211 --> 00:33:02,613
Also, onions are in season,
so they're very delicious now.

823
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:04,515
They're only in season
this time of the year.

824
00:33:04,582 --> 00:33:06,317
What are you adding? Vinegar?

825
00:33:06,384 --> 00:33:08,820
He poured vinegar on the onion.

826
00:33:08,886 --> 00:33:09,721
And cooking wine.

827
00:33:09,787 --> 00:33:11,422
It's to get rid of the sharpness quickly.

828
00:33:11,489 --> 00:33:13,558
-To remove the sharpness.
-That's smart.

829
00:33:13,925 --> 00:33:15,326
WITCH WITH A WOK GRABS GREEN ONION

830
00:33:15,693 --> 00:33:17,295
SPLIT HALFWAY

831
00:33:17,562 --> 00:33:18,663
AND CUT INTO GOOD SIZES

832
00:33:19,897 --> 00:33:21,933
THE WITCH STARTS CHOPPING NOW!

833
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:24,268
I can hear her chopping now.

834
00:33:24,335 --> 00:33:25,703
She's julienning the green onion.

835
00:33:25,770 --> 00:33:27,505
AS THIN AS THREAD

836
00:33:28,473 --> 00:33:29,407
TA-DA

837
00:33:29,474 --> 00:33:31,576
-She's unbelievably fast.
-She's so fast.

838
00:33:31,642 --> 00:33:32,944
Chop, chop.

839
00:33:33,444 --> 00:33:34,545
CUTS THE WHITE PART AT A SLIGHT ANGLE

840
00:33:34,612 --> 00:33:36,481
It sounds like someone is on a horse.

841
00:33:36,547 --> 00:33:38,049
Not only is she very fast,

842
00:33:38,116 --> 00:33:39,083
but she's also detailed.

843
00:33:39,150 --> 00:33:40,985
Next, cucumber.
She's using a cucumber too.

844
00:33:41,652 --> 00:33:43,454
She cuts it lengthwise once.

845
00:33:44,222 --> 00:33:45,256
And in half again.

846
00:33:46,257 --> 00:33:47,125
To remove the seeds?

847
00:33:47,191 --> 00:33:49,027
SLICES THE CUCUMBER SO EASILY

848
00:33:49,494 --> 00:33:51,062
HOLDING IN CHECK

849
00:33:51,329 --> 00:33:52,797
BOOSTER, UP

850
00:33:52,864 --> 00:33:55,433
Her speed is unbelievable.

851
00:33:58,036 --> 00:33:59,504
Eun-yeong can't chop as well as her.

852
00:33:59,570 --> 00:34:01,639
I'm scared.

853
00:34:01,706 --> 00:34:03,841
-She's that fast?
-Yes.

854
00:34:03,908 --> 00:34:06,911
This is something Poong can't mimic.

855
00:34:06,978 --> 00:34:08,613
CHOPPING A TOMATO SLOWLY

856
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:10,882
He added garlic cloves,
green onion, and a tomato.

857
00:34:10,948 --> 00:34:12,784
-Not green onion.
-Not green onion?

858
00:34:12,850 --> 00:34:14,485
I should add it though.

859
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:15,686
He said he should add it.

860
00:34:15,753 --> 00:34:16,621
ADDING GREEN ONION

861
00:34:16,687 --> 00:34:17,522
A bit of ginger.

862
00:34:17,755 --> 00:34:18,723
MINCED GINGER

863
00:34:18,790 --> 00:34:20,992
-Chili peppers.
-Looks like he'll grind something.

864
00:34:21,059 --> 00:34:22,527
Is that for the sauce?

865
00:34:22,593 --> 00:34:25,296
-He's making Chinese sauce.
-Chinese sauce.

866
00:34:25,663 --> 00:34:26,631
HOW DARE YOU MAKE CHINESE FOOD

867
00:34:27,065 --> 00:34:27,965
BEFORE ME?

868
00:34:29,067 --> 00:34:30,601
APPLE-OGIZE TO ME!

869
00:34:30,668 --> 00:34:31,602
Apple.

870
00:34:32,603 --> 00:34:33,805
SLICED

871
00:34:33,871 --> 00:34:35,206
TAKES THE ATTENTION AGAIN

872
00:34:35,273 --> 00:34:36,541
She doesn't even take a breather.

873
00:34:36,607 --> 00:34:38,876
If I can't chop fast,
I can always grind them!

874
00:34:40,445 --> 00:34:41,579
DEAD SILENCE

875
00:34:41,646 --> 00:34:44,949
Poong is too focused on cooking,
so he's no longer funny.

876
00:34:45,716 --> 00:34:48,352
He's better at cooking now,
and his comments are great too.

877
00:34:48,419 --> 00:34:50,555
-But he hasn't been funny.
-He's lost it.

878
00:34:50,621 --> 00:34:51,823
He's boring.

879
00:34:52,123 --> 00:34:53,357
A HARSH CRITIC

880
00:34:53,424 --> 00:34:56,594
He only says useless things now,
making my ears hurt.

881
00:34:56,661 --> 00:34:59,230
I'm sure he'll give us
some funny moments here and there.

882
00:34:59,297 --> 00:35:01,699
-He just spilled that, right?
-Yes.

883
00:35:01,766 --> 00:35:03,334
That was the funniest moment so far.

884
00:35:03,401 --> 00:35:05,369
CRITIC CHOI HYUN-SUK FUN RATING 3.5

885
00:35:05,803 --> 00:35:08,039
EVALUATING HIS EVERY MOMENT

886
00:35:08,606 --> 00:35:10,741
I'm sure he'll do something.
I have faith in him.

887
00:35:11,642 --> 00:35:13,244
It's been five minutes already.

888
00:35:14,078 --> 00:35:16,214
THIS TIME, SHE CHOPS CHILI PEPPERS!

889
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,682
She chops some chili peppers in.

890
00:35:17,748 --> 00:35:21,152
She's preparing all her ingredients first.

891
00:35:24,689 --> 00:35:25,790
SHE CHOPPED EVERYTHING AND…

892
00:35:26,491 --> 00:35:27,925
I just threw all of them out.

893
00:35:28,326 --> 00:35:29,527
CHOPPING RED CHILI PEPPERS AGAIN

894
00:35:29,594 --> 00:35:30,828
The pepper…

895
00:35:30,895 --> 00:35:33,030
-I threw them out.
-She threw out the chopped peppers.

896
00:35:33,097 --> 00:35:35,133
-Why?
-She's chopping new ones.

897
00:35:35,199 --> 00:35:37,268
-Did she not like them?
-She was too rushed.

898
00:35:37,335 --> 00:35:38,803
-It was a mistake.
-A mistake.

899
00:35:38,870 --> 00:35:39,937
It was staged.

900
00:35:40,171 --> 00:35:41,272
TO SHOW EVERYONE SHE'S ONLY HUMAN

901
00:35:41,339 --> 00:35:43,608
Chopping chili peppers isn't easy.

902
00:35:43,674 --> 00:35:45,676
She made vertical cuts first.

903
00:35:45,743 --> 00:35:47,111
CHOPPING FINELY!

904
00:35:47,178 --> 00:35:49,347
She's making tiny pieces.

905
00:35:50,281 --> 00:35:51,716
Let's see what he can do.

906
00:35:51,983 --> 00:35:53,384
HEY, LOOK AT YOU

907
00:35:53,451 --> 00:35:55,153
He's quite fast too!

908
00:35:56,487 --> 00:35:57,822
He's doing that for her to see!

909
00:35:57,889 --> 00:35:59,590
They're all different in size.

910
00:35:59,657 --> 00:36:01,259
The sizes are quite different.

911
00:36:01,325 --> 00:36:02,760
Watch your hand.

912
00:36:03,060 --> 00:36:05,363
AUTHENTIC CHEF VS. BOOTLEG CHEF

913
00:36:05,429 --> 00:36:08,499
The sizes are uniform
because Chef Moon-jung has a guide,

914
00:36:08,566 --> 00:36:11,636
but he's holding the end of it
and just making noises.

915
00:36:11,702 --> 00:36:15,706
That's why his green onion pieces
come in random sizes.

916
00:36:15,773 --> 00:36:17,575
That's pretty funny too.

917
00:36:17,775 --> 00:36:18,743
"THE CHOPPING WAS FUNNY"

918
00:36:18,809 --> 00:36:20,011
It's very funny.

919
00:36:20,077 --> 00:36:21,045
TRIGGERED

920
00:36:21,112 --> 00:36:23,548
Are you an ombudsman?
Why are you evaluating me?

921
00:36:23,614 --> 00:36:26,717
-He's good.
-He hasn't been funny lately.

922
00:36:26,784 --> 00:36:29,320
PEPPER BIBIM-JANG,
RED PEPPER POWDER, COOKING WINE

923
00:36:29,387 --> 00:36:30,388
TUNA SAUCE

924
00:36:30,454 --> 00:36:31,489
He gets triggered

925
00:36:31,556 --> 00:36:33,291
-when I point out his skills.
-He's offended.

926
00:36:33,357 --> 00:36:35,826
He should've been offended
when we called him boring.

927
00:36:36,127 --> 00:36:37,662
SAME-SIZED GREEN ONION PIECES!

928
00:36:39,497 --> 00:36:41,199
RED PEPPER POWDER, SUGAR

929
00:36:41,265 --> 00:36:43,401
OYSTER SAUCE

930
00:36:45,636 --> 00:36:46,837
SQUEEZE

931
00:36:46,904 --> 00:36:48,239
What's that sauce?

932
00:36:48,306 --> 00:36:50,641
-It's from the bibimmyeon.
-Bibimmyeon sauce.

933
00:36:50,708 --> 00:36:53,144
She just grabbed the sauce from the bag.

934
00:36:53,211 --> 00:36:54,679
DROP BOILING OIL!

935
00:36:54,745 --> 00:36:55,913
She needs chili oil,

936
00:36:55,980 --> 00:36:57,982
but I think
she's making it while making the sauce.

937
00:36:58,783 --> 00:37:01,619
That can save time. That's faster.

938
00:37:01,686 --> 00:37:03,421
We've never seen anyone do this.

939
00:37:03,487 --> 00:37:05,289
She mixed bibimmyeon sauce with chili oil.

940
00:37:05,556 --> 00:37:07,558
PREPPING WHELK BY CUTTING THEM!

941
00:37:07,625 --> 00:37:08,960
Are those whelks?

942
00:37:09,026 --> 00:37:09,860
Yes.

943
00:37:09,927 --> 00:37:11,295
-Those are whelks?
-Yes.

944
00:37:11,362 --> 00:37:13,331
She answers everything too.

945
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:15,366
You have nine minutes left.

946
00:37:15,433 --> 00:37:16,834
Six minutes have gone by.

947
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:20,805
He's grating a curry block
to mix into his frying batter.

948
00:37:21,105 --> 00:37:21,973
RIP

949
00:37:22,039 --> 00:37:23,608
He's using <i>ramyeon</i> soup base too.

950
00:37:23,674 --> 00:37:26,177
He added <i>ramyeon</i> soup base
into the frying batter.

951
00:37:26,244 --> 00:37:27,478
That and curry.

952
00:37:27,778 --> 00:37:29,247
MOON-JUNG MAKES FRYING BATTER TOO!

953
00:37:29,313 --> 00:37:30,848
She's using whelk.

954
00:37:30,915 --> 00:37:32,183
She poured starch.

955
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:33,784
-And oil?
-And cooking oil?

956
00:37:33,851 --> 00:37:35,286
-That's new.
-Chinese yam, oil, starch.

957
00:37:35,353 --> 00:37:37,188
Does the cooking oil change anything?

958
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:39,257
Oil has opposite properties from water,

959
00:37:39,323 --> 00:37:41,726
so they'll collide
and create a layer of air.

960
00:37:41,792 --> 00:37:43,628
Really? Then I'll add oil too!

961
00:37:43,894 --> 00:37:45,796
COPIES HER RECIPE

962
00:37:45,863 --> 00:37:47,698
-He'll add oil too.
-Hey, that's too much.

963
00:37:47,765 --> 00:37:50,768
He added a bit of oil
while making his frying batter.

964
00:37:50,835 --> 00:37:53,838
When you add oil to the batter,

965
00:37:53,904 --> 00:37:56,607
it'll seep out when it's fried
and create a layer of air.

966
00:37:57,508 --> 00:37:59,644
Min is really into whelk.

967
00:37:59,710 --> 00:38:01,579
She's frying them.

968
00:38:01,646 --> 00:38:03,748
She's deep-frying the whelks

969
00:38:03,814 --> 00:38:06,584
-in yam, starch, and oil batter.
-That's new.

970
00:38:06,651 --> 00:38:08,986
That's so new.

971
00:38:09,053 --> 00:38:11,188
Chinese yam batter.

972
00:38:11,689 --> 00:38:12,790
TORCH, ON

973
00:38:13,791 --> 00:38:17,962
-He's using a torch!
-He sears the mackerel with a torch.

974
00:38:18,029 --> 00:38:20,298
The skin may smell fishy,

975
00:38:20,364 --> 00:38:22,667
-so I'm removing it.
-He's removing the skin.

976
00:38:22,733 --> 00:38:23,768
You're detailed.

977
00:38:23,834 --> 00:38:25,503
He has improved a lot.

978
00:38:25,569 --> 00:38:27,405
He knows all the details.

979
00:38:27,471 --> 00:38:29,140
He could've easily done it
with boiling water.

980
00:38:29,206 --> 00:38:31,275
He can peel it off with boiling water?

981
00:38:31,342 --> 00:38:33,844
-Really?
-I guess he didn't know.

982
00:38:33,911 --> 00:38:35,246
He can just peel it too.

983
00:38:35,313 --> 00:38:36,781
Oh, he can?

984
00:38:36,847 --> 00:38:40,384
But this way,
you can remove it easier and faster.

985
00:38:40,451 --> 00:38:41,552
2. CHOP PEELED MACKEREL

986
00:38:41,619 --> 00:38:44,088
You aren't frying it in whole,
but in pieces.

987
00:38:44,155 --> 00:38:46,824
He could've deep-fried it
and then chopped it.

988
00:38:46,891 --> 00:38:49,293
-No.
-Then it'll have less surface area

989
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:51,228
-for the crispy batter.
-You're right!

990
00:38:51,295 --> 00:38:53,197
-You're right.
-I am.

991
00:38:53,264 --> 00:38:57,234
Chef Moon-jung just explained
what Poong was doing.

992
00:38:57,301 --> 00:38:59,170
I don't think of you as an enemy.

993
00:38:59,236 --> 00:39:00,738
I don't either.

994
00:39:02,139 --> 00:39:03,841
-Good luck.
-Good luck.

995
00:39:04,675 --> 00:39:06,944
-You know, right? Let's win-win.
-I know.

996
00:39:07,011 --> 00:39:09,046
-"Let's not fight."
-"My friend."

997
00:39:09,113 --> 00:39:10,581
ARE YOU ON THE SAME PAGE?

998
00:39:11,582 --> 00:39:13,484
-MSG.
-Hey.

999
00:39:13,551 --> 00:39:15,720
MSG! She added MSG!

1000
00:39:15,786 --> 00:39:17,455
What? You're using MSG?

1001
00:39:17,521 --> 00:39:19,557
-The whelk sauce.
-How can a chef do that?

1002
00:39:19,623 --> 00:39:22,026
"If she uses it, then so will I."

1003
00:39:22,326 --> 00:39:23,794
I'M A WEBTOON ARTIST, SO I'LL USE MORE

1004
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:26,097
-That's too much. It's gonna be salty.
-The whole packet.

1005
00:39:26,163 --> 00:39:28,799
She does not even back down from using MSG

1006
00:39:28,866 --> 00:39:30,568
to win this cook-off and get a star.

1007
00:39:32,036 --> 00:39:33,871
-She's chilling it.
-The sauce.

1008
00:39:33,938 --> 00:39:35,239
-Five minutes.
-Sung-ju!

1009
00:39:35,306 --> 00:39:37,875
-Yes! I'm on it!
-Can you report from the kitchen?

1010
00:39:37,942 --> 00:39:39,643
Let me check Min's food!

1011
00:39:39,710 --> 00:39:42,146
-Doesn't time fly?
-Crazy fast.

1012
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:44,348
-Poong versus Moon-jung.
-Stay calm.

1013
00:39:44,415 --> 00:39:46,183
What's that? Oh, the yam.

1014
00:39:46,250 --> 00:39:48,119
5. COAT YAM SLICES WITH POWDER
AND LINE THEM UP

1015
00:39:48,185 --> 00:39:49,653
So that's what she's doing.

1016
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:51,889
This is the sauce.

1017
00:39:51,956 --> 00:39:53,724
Let me try it.

1018
00:39:54,291 --> 00:39:56,394
Are you under the Witch's spell?

1019
00:39:56,961 --> 00:39:59,029
Are you under the Witch's spell?

1020
00:39:59,096 --> 00:40:00,631
I'm bewitched.

1021
00:40:00,698 --> 00:40:01,832
This is really good.

1022
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:04,602
YOU WILL BE SMITTEN

1023
00:40:04,668 --> 00:40:06,570
Witch With a Wok!

1024
00:40:08,072 --> 00:40:09,073
When will you make the flowers?

1025
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:11,308
-Right now.
-This is how she's making flowers!

1026
00:40:11,375 --> 00:40:12,943
-Are those the flowers?
-Yes.

1027
00:40:13,010 --> 00:40:16,013
Witch With a Wok is making Witch Flowers.

1028
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:19,483
-Shrimp.
-She's crushing the shrimp.

1029
00:40:19,550 --> 00:40:22,620
-The shrimp… It just slipped out.
-Man.

1030
00:40:22,953 --> 00:40:24,255
CRUSHING AGAIN

1031
00:40:24,321 --> 00:40:26,190
She crushes the shrimp

1032
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:28,526
-and places them on the flower.
-Like dumpling wrappers.

1033
00:40:28,592 --> 00:40:30,561
I see. She's using shrimp like that.

1034
00:40:30,628 --> 00:40:32,430
How does it turn into a flower?

1035
00:40:32,496 --> 00:40:33,564
You'll see.

1036
00:40:34,198 --> 00:40:36,100
Do I just have to wait and see?

1037
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,202
That's cool.

1038
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:40,604
She made the flower.

1039
00:40:41,405 --> 00:40:43,641
It reminds me of a tulip.

1040
00:40:43,707 --> 00:40:45,276
Like a tulip.

1041
00:40:45,342 --> 00:40:47,578
My gosh. It turned into a flower.

1042
00:40:47,645 --> 00:40:49,480
That's so cool.

1043
00:40:49,547 --> 00:40:51,048
She takes the whelks out.

1044
00:40:51,115 --> 00:40:54,151
She's about to deep-fry the flower.
I hope it stays intact.

1045
00:40:54,218 --> 00:40:56,253
She's holding it with the tongs.

1046
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:57,455
She's holding it tight.

1047
00:40:57,521 --> 00:40:59,657
The slices were thicker than I thought.

1048
00:40:59,723 --> 00:41:01,325
I see. It could've been better.

1049
00:41:02,793 --> 00:41:04,762
-It's coming undone.
-You missed it.

1050
00:41:04,829 --> 00:41:07,398
-It's okay. That's why I prepared two.
-Is it?

1051
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:09,233
It's a bit thicker than she wanted.

1052
00:41:09,667 --> 00:41:11,268
THIS IS POONG'S CHANCE!

1053
00:41:11,335 --> 00:41:13,504
-What's this?
-It's the sauce.

1054
00:41:13,571 --> 00:41:14,705
For what?

1055
00:41:14,772 --> 00:41:16,340
I'll serve it with the fried mackerel.

1056
00:41:16,407 --> 00:41:19,009
It smells like <i>kimchi-jjigae</i>, the stew.

1057
00:41:19,076 --> 00:41:21,078
Let me try this.

1058
00:41:21,145 --> 00:41:23,147
Will it make the Witch

1059
00:41:23,214 --> 00:41:24,915
cry a river?

1060
00:41:25,216 --> 00:41:27,885
WILL SHE CRY A RIVER?

1061
00:41:27,952 --> 00:41:30,955
I don't think it's quite there yet.

1062
00:41:31,021 --> 00:41:33,757
You need some more umami.
It's not quite there yet.

1063
00:41:33,824 --> 00:41:35,493
Two minutes and ten seconds!

1064
00:41:35,559 --> 00:41:37,795
Time really flies.

1065
00:41:38,095 --> 00:41:38,929
ALLULOSE

1066
00:41:40,264 --> 00:41:41,265
CHILI OIL

1067
00:41:41,499 --> 00:41:43,701
7. STIR-FRY FRIED WHELKS
WITH ALLULOSE AND CHILI OIL

1068
00:41:43,767 --> 00:41:45,402
The whelks are ready.

1069
00:41:45,469 --> 00:41:47,872
-Right.
-Moon-jung takes the whelks out.

1070
00:41:48,506 --> 00:41:49,940
4. BLEND AVOCADO AND CONDIMENTS

1071
00:41:50,007 --> 00:41:51,442
A bit of mayonnaise.

1072
00:41:51,509 --> 00:41:53,544
Yogurt. Crushed garlic.
This is another sauce.

1073
00:41:53,611 --> 00:41:56,447
It's like… What was that? Tzatziki?

1074
00:41:56,514 --> 00:41:58,816
He's topping something on the onion.

1075
00:41:58,883 --> 00:42:01,018
He's starting to plate the dish.

1076
00:42:01,085 --> 00:42:04,255
-He's putting the sauce on the onion.
-Yes.

1077
00:42:04,321 --> 00:42:05,623
Let me taste it.

1078
00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:07,625
What's this sauce like?

1079
00:42:07,691 --> 00:42:08,792
CHECKING THE CREAM SAUCE!

1080
00:42:09,326 --> 00:42:11,228
Does it make you want to chug <i>somaek</i>?

1081
00:42:11,295 --> 00:42:12,796
It makes me want to chug it!

1082
00:42:12,863 --> 00:42:14,532
-Chug it!
-This is nice.

1083
00:42:14,598 --> 00:42:16,967
I like this refreshing sauce on the onion.

1084
00:42:17,034 --> 00:42:18,903
I'm trying to maximize
the sweetness of the onion.

1085
00:42:18,969 --> 00:42:21,772
It's to maximize
the sweetness of the onion.

1086
00:42:21,839 --> 00:42:25,376
-You have a minute left now!
-One minute.

1087
00:42:25,442 --> 00:42:27,511
You have to hurry up and wrap up.

1088
00:42:27,578 --> 00:42:29,747
-He gets the mackerel out.
-One minute.

1089
00:42:29,813 --> 00:42:33,350
-The mackerel comes out.
-They look so crispy.

1090
00:42:33,417 --> 00:42:35,219
One minute.

1091
00:42:35,419 --> 00:42:37,054
MAYONNAISE & CHILI PEPPER

1092
00:42:37,121 --> 00:42:38,255
Dang it. This thing!

1093
00:42:38,322 --> 00:42:40,157
You have to hurry up and wrap up.

1094
00:42:40,224 --> 00:42:41,759
Hurry up.

1095
00:42:41,825 --> 00:42:43,627
That's Sriracha.

1096
00:42:43,861 --> 00:42:45,229
LEMON JUICE, CHILI OIL

1097
00:42:45,296 --> 00:42:47,898
THE BASE SAUCE ON THE BOTTOM

1098
00:42:47,965 --> 00:42:51,035
That's the flower Moon-jung made!

1099
00:42:51,101 --> 00:42:52,903
-I hope they look good.
-They should.

1100
00:42:52,970 --> 00:42:54,505
-Witch Flowers.
-The flowers.

1101
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:56,907
Moon-jung is in a hurry too.

1102
00:42:56,974 --> 00:42:58,943
I guess that's the side dish.

1103
00:42:59,944 --> 00:43:01,645
She's no longer talking.

1104
00:43:01,712 --> 00:43:03,981
They both deep-fried something,
so it's better to finish first.

1105
00:43:04,048 --> 00:43:06,717
-Yes. She drops the whelks!
-Thirty seconds!

1106
00:43:06,784 --> 00:43:09,520
She made a cold whelk salad!

1107
00:43:09,587 --> 00:43:12,089
-You have 30 seconds left!
-You have no time.

1108
00:43:12,690 --> 00:43:13,691
POONG FINISHES UP TOO

1109
00:43:14,325 --> 00:43:17,661
PLATING THE MACKEREL FRITTERS!

1110
00:43:17,728 --> 00:43:20,164
-Twenty-five seconds. Twenty.
-Twenty seconds.

1111
00:43:21,165 --> 00:43:22,733
Poong's almost done.

1112
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:24,201
Twenty seconds.

1113
00:43:24,735 --> 00:43:26,437
Moon-jung looks busy!

1114
00:43:26,503 --> 00:43:29,373
Fifteen seconds. Poong's almost done.

1115
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:30,941
-Ten. Nine. Eight. Seven.
-Seven.

1116
00:43:31,008 --> 00:43:32,309
-Six.
-Six.

1117
00:43:32,376 --> 00:43:34,345
He just has to pour the sauce.

1118
00:43:34,411 --> 00:43:36,347
Just pour the sauce.

1119
00:43:36,413 --> 00:43:39,249
-Ten. Nine. Eight. Seven. Six.
-Seven. Six.

1120
00:43:40,184 --> 00:43:43,487
PLATING THE COLD WHELK SALAD!

1121
00:43:44,488 --> 00:43:46,090
WHO'LL FINISH FIRST?

1122
00:43:46,156 --> 00:43:47,324
-One!
-One!

1123
00:43:47,391 --> 00:43:51,128
-Time's up! Poong finishes first.
-It's over.

1124
00:43:51,195 --> 00:43:54,064
-You can no longer cook.
-You can only plate it.

1125
00:43:54,131 --> 00:43:55,899
You can't make anything new.

1126
00:43:55,966 --> 00:43:57,835
You can't do anything new.

1127
00:43:57,901 --> 00:44:00,137
That's all you can do. That's it.

1128
00:44:00,204 --> 00:44:02,172
I got something… I got sweat in my eye.

1129
00:44:02,239 --> 00:44:03,641
He's about to cry a river!

1130
00:44:03,707 --> 00:44:05,843
Sweat is flowing into my eye!

1131
00:44:05,909 --> 00:44:09,179
-You're sweating too much!
-And I'm crying a river!

1132
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:12,149
CRITIC HYUN-SUK
"BECAME FUNNY AFTER HE STOPPED COOKING"

1133
00:44:12,216 --> 00:44:14,852
Both dishes are finished.

1134
00:44:14,918 --> 00:44:16,787
The Somaek.

1135
00:44:17,688 --> 00:44:19,490
That looks good.

1136
00:44:19,556 --> 00:44:22,226
AMAZED

1137
00:44:23,293 --> 00:44:24,762
People should see this in person.

1138
00:44:24,828 --> 00:44:27,765
It's a shame
that only we got to watch them cook.

1139
00:44:27,831 --> 00:44:30,734
It's so different in real life
compared to what I saw on TV.

1140
00:44:30,801 --> 00:44:32,436
-Completely.
-So different.

1141
00:44:32,503 --> 00:44:35,005
-That was shocking.
-They were so cool.

1142
00:44:35,072 --> 00:44:37,474
Both dishes for The Somaek

1143
00:44:37,541 --> 00:44:40,177
have been made for you, Min.

1144
00:44:40,244 --> 00:44:41,679
While you watched them cook,

1145
00:44:41,745 --> 00:44:43,981
-you didn't look so…
-You looked serious.

1146
00:44:44,048 --> 00:44:47,317
-How can I put it? I was fascinated.
-He's right.

1147
00:44:47,384 --> 00:44:50,054
-It was something I've never seen before.
-Right.

1148
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:52,222
I was surprised and in shock.

1149
00:44:52,289 --> 00:44:53,791
It was a great experience.

1150
00:44:53,857 --> 00:44:56,293
You also look surprised, Dae-myung.

1151
00:44:56,360 --> 00:44:57,528
When the 15 minutes began,

1152
00:44:57,594 --> 00:45:00,097
both their eyes changed,

1153
00:45:00,164 --> 00:45:01,865
and they're back now.

1154
00:45:01,932 --> 00:45:03,167
DID A FULL TURN AND BACK

1155
00:45:03,233 --> 00:45:05,769
Poong finished first, right?

1156
00:45:05,836 --> 00:45:07,538
Please try his dish,

1157
00:45:07,604 --> 00:45:09,573
<i>Mackerel Will Make You Chug Somaek</i>!

1158
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:10,708
MACKEREL FRITTER AND SAUCE!

1159
00:45:11,041 --> 00:45:14,278
SERVED WITH ONION WRAPS AND SPECIAL SAUCE

1160
00:45:14,611 --> 00:45:18,248
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
MACKEREL WILL MAKE YOU CHUG SOMAEK!

1161
00:45:18,315 --> 00:45:20,584
-How do I eat this?
-How should he eat it?

1162
00:45:20,651 --> 00:45:22,720
Put a piece of onion on your spoon.

1163
00:45:22,786 --> 00:45:26,990
Then put a piece of fritter
covered with sauce and eat it at once.

1164
00:45:27,057 --> 00:45:29,493
If I eat it like this…

1165
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:30,694
It's huge.

1166
00:45:30,761 --> 00:45:32,029
-Mackerel fritters.
-Yes.

1167
00:45:32,096 --> 00:45:34,298
Just think of that as one wrap.

1168
00:45:34,364 --> 00:45:35,799
He eats it right away.

1169
00:45:37,367 --> 00:45:39,937
It's something that you gobble down.

1170
00:45:40,270 --> 00:45:41,872
AS ALWAYS, DROOLING

1171
00:45:41,939 --> 00:45:44,041
I wonder what the sauce is like.

1172
00:45:44,608 --> 00:45:48,645
There is a bit of spiciness

1173
00:45:48,712 --> 00:45:50,981
<i>that reminds me of Chinese food.</i>

1174
00:45:51,048 --> 00:45:54,451
But the onion isn't like
the usual thing we imagine.

1175
00:45:54,518 --> 00:45:57,221
It's crunchy yet mild,

1176
00:45:57,287 --> 00:45:59,423
and the onion flavor isn't too strong.

1177
00:45:59,490 --> 00:46:01,358
I can taste many different flavors.

1178
00:46:01,425 --> 00:46:02,826
-It's delicious.
-Thanks.

1179
00:46:02,893 --> 00:46:05,596
I wanted to bring out
the onion's sweetness,

1180
00:46:05,662 --> 00:46:09,633
-so I made the sauce less sweet.
-I see.

1181
00:46:09,700 --> 00:46:11,268
-That's not his usual style.
-I knew it.

1182
00:46:11,335 --> 00:46:12,703
-That's odd.
-It wasn't as sweet.

1183
00:46:12,770 --> 00:46:14,438
Poong, return to your old self.

1184
00:46:14,505 --> 00:46:17,741
That dish was strictly made
to be eaten with <i>somaek.</i>

1185
00:46:17,808 --> 00:46:20,310
-Why don't you make the drink?
-Sure.

1186
00:46:20,377 --> 00:46:22,780
Hasn't it been a while
since you had <i>somaek</i> and fried food?

1187
00:46:22,846 --> 00:46:23,947
How do you take it?

1188
00:46:24,014 --> 00:46:26,350
Me? About this much.

1189
00:46:26,416 --> 00:46:27,951
-Half the cup?
-Yes.

1190
00:46:28,218 --> 00:46:30,020
THE EXPERT'S JARGON

1191
00:46:30,087 --> 00:46:32,022
Pour it!

1192
00:46:32,089 --> 00:46:34,224
So that he'll get a taste of it.

1193
00:46:34,858 --> 00:46:36,493
Do you want me to shake it?

1194
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:38,529
HIS EXTRAORDINARY GESTURE

1195
00:46:38,829 --> 00:46:40,297
LIKE THIS

1196
00:46:40,564 --> 00:46:42,399
THE HALF-SOJU HALF-BEER

1197
00:46:42,466 --> 00:46:46,637
I'll have a sip of <i>somaek</i>,
and then eat this.

1198
00:46:47,671 --> 00:46:50,274
CHUGGING

1199
00:46:50,340 --> 00:46:51,642
BOTTOMS UP

1200
00:46:52,776 --> 00:46:53,777
That was like an ad.

1201
00:46:53,844 --> 00:46:56,079
That was my first drop in 23 days.

1202
00:46:56,146 --> 00:46:57,581
-It must taste so sweet.
-Yes.

1203
00:46:57,648 --> 00:46:59,049
It'll bring out the sweetness.

1204
00:46:59,783 --> 00:47:02,452
That was his first <i>somaek </i>in 23 days.

1205
00:47:05,189 --> 00:47:08,625
Will it taste different
when he eats it with <i>somaek</i>?

1206
00:47:09,593 --> 00:47:11,662
Now that I eat it with <i>somaek</i>,

1207
00:47:11,728 --> 00:47:13,931
unlike the bite I had before,

1208
00:47:13,997 --> 00:47:16,700
the spiciness has dwindled down.

1209
00:47:16,767 --> 00:47:19,269
-It's a bit sweeter.
-You're right.

1210
00:47:19,336 --> 00:47:22,406
It's because I tuned the flavor to <i>somaek.</i>

1211
00:47:22,472 --> 00:47:24,241
I wanted you to
taste the onion's sweetness.

1212
00:47:24,308 --> 00:47:26,043
Poong did that?

1213
00:47:26,109 --> 00:47:28,345
-It's sweet.
-Isn't it?

1214
00:47:28,412 --> 00:47:29,479
Maybe it's the drink.

1215
00:47:30,047 --> 00:47:31,582
That might be the case.

1216
00:47:31,648 --> 00:47:34,218
-You haven't had a drink in a while.
-Right.

1217
00:47:34,284 --> 00:47:35,152
It's so delicious.

1218
00:47:35,219 --> 00:47:37,087
Do you mean that it goes well with <i>somaek</i>?

1219
00:47:37,154 --> 00:47:39,890
I'll try the other one
before I make my evaluation.

1220
00:47:39,957 --> 00:47:42,526
I'll have to be the judge and decide

1221
00:47:42,593 --> 00:47:44,962
which one was more attune to the topic.

1222
00:47:45,028 --> 00:47:47,898
Next, Chef Moon-jung's dish,

1223
00:47:47,965 --> 00:47:49,633
<i>Abracadabooze, AlakaChineseYam.</i>

1224
00:47:49,700 --> 00:47:51,668
THE REBIRTH OF WHELK SALAD
WITH A TOUCH OF MAGIC

1225
00:47:52,135 --> 00:47:54,638
SERVED WITH WITCH FLOWERS MADE WITH YAM

1226
00:47:54,972 --> 00:47:58,508
CHEF YI MOON-JUNG'S
ABRACADABOOZE, ALAKACHINESEYAM

1227
00:47:58,575 --> 00:48:01,445
There are lots of complicated things here,

1228
00:48:01,511 --> 00:48:03,947
-so I'm not sure where to begin.
-I wonder.

1229
00:48:04,014 --> 00:48:05,949
May I serve it for you?

1230
00:48:06,016 --> 00:48:09,253
She came and served her dish
last time she was here.

1231
00:48:09,720 --> 00:48:10,554
MAKING HER CASE NEARBY

1232
00:48:10,621 --> 00:48:12,656
<i>As she served the food here…</i>

1233
00:48:12,723 --> 00:48:14,658
-She chats.
-…she said something to him.

1234
00:48:14,725 --> 00:48:16,760
I must always think this is the last.

1235
00:48:16,827 --> 00:48:18,462
All right.

1236
00:48:18,528 --> 00:48:19,363
-Okay.
-Thank you.

1237
00:48:19,429 --> 00:48:21,698
ROCK-SOLID DEFENSE

1238
00:48:22,366 --> 00:48:24,067
PURGED

1239
00:48:26,570 --> 00:48:29,706
She may try to cheat,
so let's get her on camera.

1240
00:48:29,773 --> 00:48:31,675
The way you eat it is important.

1241
00:48:31,742 --> 00:48:35,879
-Dip it in a lot of sauce and try it.
-This one?

1242
00:48:35,946 --> 00:48:37,481
The flower? It looks like one.

1243
00:48:38,348 --> 00:48:40,017
-Eat it just like that.
-Try it.

1244
00:48:40,651 --> 00:48:42,486
And next, the whelks.

1245
00:48:42,819 --> 00:48:45,322
SUPER FOCUSED

1246
00:48:45,389 --> 00:48:49,059
Apple and vegetables.

1247
00:48:49,126 --> 00:48:51,728
It doesn't look like
she's doing anything special.

1248
00:48:51,795 --> 00:48:54,798
-He could've done that himself.
-She's just grabbing everything.

1249
00:48:54,865 --> 00:48:58,268
Can you keep an eye on her and see
if she's bribing him with money?

1250
00:48:59,436 --> 00:49:01,138
JINGLE JINGLE

1251
00:49:01,939 --> 00:49:03,440
GIVES HIM THE SPOON INSTEAD OF MONEY

1252
00:49:03,507 --> 00:49:07,577
Manager Park also fell for this last time.

1253
00:49:07,644 --> 00:49:09,179
I think you lost.

1254
00:49:09,246 --> 00:49:10,747
You should've served the wrap.

1255
00:49:10,814 --> 00:49:12,316
This time,

1256
00:49:12,382 --> 00:49:15,052
-you can dip this in that sauce.
-Okay.

1257
00:49:15,118 --> 00:49:17,554
That's time, Moon-jung.

1258
00:49:19,122 --> 00:49:22,693
Yes, the Witch has a way
of bewitching the guests.

1259
00:49:22,759 --> 00:49:23,894
Right?

1260
00:49:24,461 --> 00:49:25,495
What's it like?

1261
00:49:25,996 --> 00:49:27,230
Right now…

1262
00:49:27,297 --> 00:49:29,166
When I tried this,

1263
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:33,036
it didn't taste like Chinese yam,
but the sauce

1264
00:49:33,103 --> 00:49:36,073
surprised me as soon as I tried it.

1265
00:49:36,139 --> 00:49:38,408
-The sauce on the dish?
-Yes.

1266
00:49:38,475 --> 00:49:41,611
These are whelks that had been fried,

1267
00:49:41,678 --> 00:49:43,613
smothered in spicy sauce.

1268
00:49:43,680 --> 00:49:46,616
It has the essence
of the ordinary whelk salad,

1269
00:49:46,683 --> 00:49:52,022
but with the addition
of many other flavors.

1270
00:49:52,089 --> 00:49:54,324
An upgrade to it? A classier version?

1271
00:49:54,391 --> 00:49:56,727
Whelks we usually eat have a crunch to it,

1272
00:49:56,793 --> 00:50:00,130
<i>but these weren't.</i>
<i>They were mostly tender.</i>

1273
00:50:00,197 --> 00:50:01,732
<i>The squishy texture</i>

1274
00:50:01,798 --> 00:50:04,568
helped me enjoy the flavor
for much longer.

1275
00:50:04,634 --> 00:50:06,670
Why don't you try that with <i>somaek</i> too?

1276
00:50:06,737 --> 00:50:08,338
Yes, I'd love to.

1277
00:50:08,405 --> 00:50:09,806
I've already had a drink, so…

1278
00:50:09,873 --> 00:50:11,108
One more drink.

1279
00:50:11,174 --> 00:50:12,776
You can pour it yourself.

1280
00:50:12,843 --> 00:50:15,679
Yes, of course. I'll make my own drink.

1281
00:50:15,746 --> 00:50:18,582
-No, Jung-hwan. I'm fine.
-I was messing with you.

1282
00:50:18,648 --> 00:50:19,683
Thanks, Jung-hwan.

1283
00:50:19,750 --> 00:50:21,284
-That's about it.
-That's it.

1284
00:50:21,351 --> 00:50:23,687
-A swirl. Should I flip it?
-Thanks.

1285
00:50:23,754 --> 00:50:24,988
Thank you!

1286
00:50:25,689 --> 00:50:28,959
He'll try it again with <i>somaek</i>.

1287
00:50:29,026 --> 00:50:30,193
That must be good.

1288
00:50:30,260 --> 00:50:32,396
BOTTOMS UP

1289
00:50:32,462 --> 00:50:34,364
-It must be good.
-It must be.

1290
00:50:34,431 --> 00:50:36,333
-He makes it look like an ad.
-Yes.

1291
00:50:36,400 --> 00:50:37,934
Let me try this again.

1292
00:50:38,001 --> 00:50:41,271
-He must like the Witch Flower better.
-Witch Flower.

1293
00:50:41,338 --> 00:50:43,407
AGAIN, IN ONE BITE

1294
00:50:46,443 --> 00:50:48,412
IS IT GOOD WITH SOMAEK?

1295
00:50:48,478 --> 00:50:49,913
It doesn't taste like yam.

1296
00:50:49,980 --> 00:50:52,382
It doesn't seem like yam. It's so tender.

1297
00:50:52,449 --> 00:50:53,617
Maybe because it's fried?

1298
00:50:53,683 --> 00:50:56,820
Chinese yams
become soft like potatoes when cooked.

1299
00:50:56,887 --> 00:51:00,857
<i>You're right.</i>
<i>It tastes a bit like potatoes.</i>

1300
00:51:01,925 --> 00:51:03,260
-It's so good.
-It's good?

1301
00:51:03,527 --> 00:51:05,028
ALSO DELICIOUS WITH SOMAEK

1302
00:51:05,095 --> 00:51:06,296
Don't you want some?

1303
00:51:06,363 --> 00:51:07,631
-What?
-You should have a taste.

1304
00:51:07,697 --> 00:51:09,433
-Yes.
-You should try it.

1305
00:51:09,499 --> 00:51:11,134
First, try Poong's dish,

1306
00:51:11,201 --> 00:51:14,438
Mackerel Will Make You Chug Somaek.

1307
00:51:14,504 --> 00:51:18,141
ADDICTED TO ONION WRAPS

1308
00:51:18,208 --> 00:51:19,209
It's good.

1309
00:51:19,843 --> 00:51:21,478
This goes so well with mackerel.

1310
00:51:22,079 --> 00:51:23,680
SHALL I DIG IN?

1311
00:51:23,747 --> 00:51:24,948
I'll cut it into pieces.

1312
00:51:25,015 --> 00:51:25,849
A BIG PILE

1313
00:51:26,483 --> 00:51:28,718
YUM

1314
00:51:29,152 --> 00:51:31,988
EATS EVERYTHING, INCLUDING THE ONION WRAP

1315
00:51:32,355 --> 00:51:34,458
SAVORING

1316
00:51:34,791 --> 00:51:35,826
HOW WILL DAE-MYUNG LIKE IT?

1317
00:51:35,892 --> 00:51:38,428
-What do you think, Dae-myung?
-It's so delicious.

1318
00:51:38,495 --> 00:51:40,430
It almost felt like a fruit wrap.

1319
00:51:40,497 --> 00:51:41,731
THE ONION WAS LIKE FRUIT

1320
00:51:41,798 --> 00:51:44,835
The onion is cold,
while the fritters are hot,

1321
00:51:44,901 --> 00:51:47,604
-so… How do I say this?
-Say it accurately.

1322
00:51:47,671 --> 00:51:51,541
Let's say I was tanning for an hour
on the beach in Southeast Asia

1323
00:51:51,608 --> 00:51:53,810
and then got to jump into the sea.

1324
00:51:53,877 --> 00:51:56,413
How do you have such awesome analogies?

1325
00:51:56,480 --> 00:51:58,548
Were you trying to do that, Poong?

1326
00:51:58,615 --> 00:52:01,284
I couldn't even imagine.

1327
00:52:01,351 --> 00:52:03,453
But it sounds about right.

1328
00:52:03,520 --> 00:52:06,189
Chef Jong-won is good at food reviews.

1329
00:52:06,256 --> 00:52:08,825
-Say something.
-Dae-myung just gave a good review.

1330
00:52:08,892 --> 00:52:10,894
-They're pressuring him.
-Anything good?

1331
00:52:11,461 --> 00:52:12,729
In Italy,

1332
00:52:12,796 --> 00:52:15,599
prosciutto is often served with melon.

1333
00:52:15,665 --> 00:52:18,401
It reminds me of the beaches in Naples.

1334
00:52:18,468 --> 00:52:20,403
At the beaches in Naples.

1335
00:52:20,737 --> 00:52:22,672
SO MUCH PRESSURE

1336
00:52:23,006 --> 00:52:24,941
YOU GOT THIS! STAY STRONG!

1337
00:52:25,175 --> 00:52:26,710
HIGH HOPES

1338
00:52:26,776 --> 00:52:30,180
It's like I ordered sweet
and spicy chicken on the beach in Naples.

1339
00:52:32,482 --> 00:52:34,551
-Sweet and spicy chicken.
-Naples has good Chinese food.

1340
00:52:34,618 --> 00:52:36,253
Can you order delivery?

1341
00:52:36,319 --> 00:52:39,055
Sweet and spicy chicken
on the beach in Naples.

1342
00:52:39,122 --> 00:52:43,160
Next, Chef Moon-jung's dish,
Abracadabooze, AlakaChineseYam.

1343
00:52:45,729 --> 00:52:47,764
This is so pretty.

1344
00:52:47,831 --> 00:52:50,534
It's like a dark rose
blooming on the field.

1345
00:52:51,501 --> 00:52:53,303
A NEW EPOCH OF REVIEWS

1346
00:52:53,370 --> 00:52:56,139
It smells captivating.

1347
00:52:56,206 --> 00:52:59,376
Min slowly looks back on what he said.

1348
00:52:59,442 --> 00:53:02,579
-We forgot everything.
-He's like, "Should I do it over?"

1349
00:53:02,646 --> 00:53:06,049
Dae-myung's reviews are like poetry.

1350
00:53:06,116 --> 00:53:07,551
What's it like, Dae-myung?

1351
00:53:08,418 --> 00:53:09,653
Where are we going now?

1352
00:53:09,719 --> 00:53:11,254
WHERE IS HE GOING TO?

1353
00:53:11,821 --> 00:53:14,291
-It's the neighborhood hill.
-The nearby hill?

1354
00:53:14,357 --> 00:53:15,692
A flavor from a nearby hill.

1355
00:53:15,759 --> 00:53:17,827
The thing is, I saw the black rose.

1356
00:53:17,894 --> 00:53:20,063
Should I grab it or not?
I mean, it'll sting.

1357
00:53:20,330 --> 00:53:21,431
IT HAS THORNS…

1358
00:53:21,498 --> 00:53:22,599
-The thorns.
-Right.

1359
00:53:22,666 --> 00:53:24,167
I finally grabbed it,

1360
00:53:24,234 --> 00:53:25,835
but it just remained so sweet.

1361
00:53:25,902 --> 00:53:27,204
It tastes like that.

1362
00:53:27,537 --> 00:53:29,072
VERY PROUD

1363
00:53:29,139 --> 00:53:32,008
-Nam-no.
-The whelks were fried in batter

1364
00:53:32,075 --> 00:53:36,112
made with Chinese yams,
so it sucked the sauce in even better.

1365
00:53:36,179 --> 00:53:39,115
-And the green onion makes it taste fresh.
-Fresh.

1366
00:53:39,182 --> 00:53:41,518
-It's now time to choose.
-Yes.

1367
00:53:41,585 --> 00:53:43,386
Min's choice.

1368
00:53:43,453 --> 00:53:46,556
<i>Press one to pick Yi Moon-jung's</i>
<i>Abracadabooze, AlakaChineseYam.</i>

1369
00:53:46,623 --> 00:53:50,560
<i>Press two to choose Kim Poong's</i>
<i>Mackerel Will Make You Chug Somaek.</i>

1370
00:53:51,494 --> 00:53:53,663
-I pressed it.
-You did?

1371
00:53:53,730 --> 00:53:56,333
I guess it wasn't a difficult choice.

1372
00:53:56,399 --> 00:53:57,601
I'm scared.

1373
00:53:57,667 --> 00:53:59,302
Wasn't I supposed to press it right away?

1374
00:53:59,369 --> 00:54:02,372
It can lead to misunderstandings
and make people go, "So it was easy."

1375
00:54:02,439 --> 00:54:04,507
-Wait.
-Some go, "I can't choose one."

1376
00:54:04,574 --> 00:54:06,676
Wait a second. Let me do it over.

1377
00:54:06,743 --> 00:54:07,911
Let's do that scene.

1378
00:54:09,112 --> 00:54:11,114
-He's torn.
-It's a tough decision.

1379
00:54:11,181 --> 00:54:12,415
-It's not easy.
-He's so torn.

1380
00:54:12,682 --> 00:54:15,318
MIN FALLS DEEP IN THOUGHT
BEFORE MAKING A CHOICE

1381
00:54:15,385 --> 00:54:18,121
It's a tough decision!

1382
00:54:18,388 --> 00:54:19,789
ALSO GETTING EXCITED

1383
00:54:19,856 --> 00:54:21,424
Yes, I pressed it.

1384
00:54:21,491 --> 00:54:23,360
-Oh, finally.
-Finally.

1385
00:54:23,627 --> 00:54:25,295
HE SURELY IS A GOOD ACTOR

1386
00:54:25,362 --> 00:54:28,565
The winner of the Grand Award in acting
is definitely different.

1387
00:54:28,632 --> 00:54:30,567
Let's find out the winner.

1388
00:54:30,634 --> 00:54:33,503
Who did Min choose?

1389
00:54:33,570 --> 00:54:34,938
Show us!

1390
00:54:35,005 --> 00:54:36,139
The Somaek.

1391
00:54:36,206 --> 00:54:38,041
Will it be Kim Poong,
the gatekeeper of the show?

1392
00:54:38,108 --> 00:54:40,377
Or will it be Yi Moon-jung,
aka Witch With a Wok?

1393
00:54:40,443 --> 00:54:42,612
Who did he choose?

1394
00:54:42,679 --> 00:54:43,880
Which one is it?

1395
00:54:43,947 --> 00:54:45,715
Which <i>somaek</i> snack?

1396
00:54:45,782 --> 00:54:47,083
Who was chosen?

1397
00:54:47,150 --> 00:54:49,019
What's the result?

1398
00:54:49,252 --> 00:54:50,487
YI MOON-JUNG WINS

1399
00:54:50,553 --> 00:54:52,722
ABRACADABOOZE, ALAKACHINESEYAM WINS

1400
00:54:52,956 --> 00:54:54,624
THAT WAS A GREAT MATCH

1401
00:54:54,691 --> 00:54:57,794
Witch With a Wok's second win in a row.

1402
00:54:57,861 --> 00:55:00,196
Why did you choose her dish?

1403
00:55:00,263 --> 00:55:03,300
Of course, both dishes were delicious.

1404
00:55:03,366 --> 00:55:08,505
But the dish she made
had such unexpected flavors.

1405
00:55:08,571 --> 00:55:11,374
That kind of surprise

1406
00:55:11,441 --> 00:55:14,678
made me think her dish was more delicious.

1407
00:55:14,744 --> 00:55:18,248
This means Chef Moon-jung came twice

1408
00:55:18,315 --> 00:55:21,785
and already took two stars.

1409
00:55:21,851 --> 00:55:24,454
She has more stars than Nam-no.

1410
00:55:24,521 --> 00:55:27,457
She surpasses Nam-no
just after two shoots.

1411
00:55:27,524 --> 00:55:29,926
What have I done this year?

1412
00:55:29,993 --> 00:55:32,062
Poong, you've slowed down a bit.

1413
00:55:32,128 --> 00:55:33,763
She got past me.

1414
00:55:33,830 --> 00:55:35,198
Someone stop her!

1415
00:55:35,265 --> 00:55:39,069
Chefs! She got past me!

1416
00:55:39,135 --> 00:55:42,372
-You have to stop her now.
-He couldn't stop her.

1417
00:55:42,439 --> 00:55:45,108
-He did his best.
-This is as far as I can go.

1418
00:55:45,375 --> 00:55:46,509
WHO WILL STOP THE WITCH?

1419
00:55:46,576 --> 00:55:50,580
Please put a star on Chef Moon-jung!

1420
00:55:50,814 --> 00:55:52,248
YI MOON-JUNG GETS HER 2ND STAR

1421
00:55:52,315 --> 00:55:55,518
-Moon-jung's second win in a row.
-Thank you.

1422
00:55:55,585 --> 00:55:58,455
She receives a star from Min!

1423
00:55:58,521 --> 00:55:59,689
Two wins in a row.

1424
00:55:59,756 --> 00:56:03,860
<i>This is the second cook-off</i>
<i>played with Min's ingredients.</i>

1425
00:56:03,927 --> 00:56:06,863
They're about to start a cook-off
to make something

1426
00:56:06,930 --> 00:56:10,100
that'll make Min look uglier,
titled The Ugliness.

1427
00:56:10,166 --> 00:56:13,970
-The cute Iberico pig, Yoon Nam-no…
-The ones that feed on acorns.

1428
00:56:14,037 --> 00:56:16,206
…versus a nicely formed piece of <i>sujebi</i>,

1429
00:56:16,272 --> 00:56:19,509
-Chef Kwon Sung-jun.
-<i>Sujebi?</i>

1430
00:56:20,777 --> 00:56:22,245
He's uglier than me.

1431
00:56:22,312 --> 00:56:23,780
That's quite unpleasant to hear.

1432
00:56:24,147 --> 00:56:25,448
TRIGGERED SUJEBI

1433
00:56:25,515 --> 00:56:27,183
He lost some weight recently,

1434
00:56:27,250 --> 00:56:30,387
-so he was feeling confident.
-I look likable.

1435
00:56:30,453 --> 00:56:32,288
Well, looks are one thing,

1436
00:56:32,355 --> 00:56:34,691
but these Tubby Twins each have one star.

1437
00:56:34,758 --> 00:56:38,595
One is bigger, which means five wins,
but the other is just a normal star.

1438
00:56:38,661 --> 00:56:40,263
What's going on, Nam-no?

1439
00:56:40,330 --> 00:56:44,367
I continue to fail
to figure out what the topic is about.

1440
00:56:44,434 --> 00:56:47,103
You're now behind Chef Moon-jung.

1441
00:56:47,170 --> 00:56:48,571
-Oh, no.
-What a shame.

1442
00:56:48,638 --> 00:56:51,040
On the other hand, Chef Sung-jun

1443
00:56:51,107 --> 00:56:53,977
-has won four times in a row.
-Five stars.

1444
00:56:54,043 --> 00:56:56,045
-Had he been waiting to do this?
-You're on a roll.

1445
00:56:56,112 --> 00:56:59,849
You said you believe Nam-no
didn't understand this topic either.

1446
00:56:59,916 --> 00:57:01,217
READING IT AGAIN

1447
00:57:01,284 --> 00:57:03,553
He needs to know what it feels like
to be bloated

1448
00:57:03,620 --> 00:57:05,388
or to have your skin break out
after eating something.

1449
00:57:05,455 --> 00:57:07,056
However, Chef Nam-no

1450
00:57:07,123 --> 00:57:10,059
remains bloated round-the-clock,
in every season of the year.

1451
00:57:10,126 --> 00:57:11,728
He doesn't know what did it.

1452
00:57:12,028 --> 00:57:12,962
HITS HOME

1453
00:57:13,029 --> 00:57:16,032
He has no idea why he looks bloated.

1454
00:57:16,099 --> 00:57:19,235
I do not think it'll be easy
for him to figure out the topic.

1455
00:57:19,302 --> 00:57:21,371
-He had to have the ups and downs.
-Exactly.

1456
00:57:21,438 --> 00:57:23,039
-He doesn't know.
-He doesn't have that.

1457
00:57:23,106 --> 00:57:27,677
So to figure out this topic,
he needs to have been good-looking,

1458
00:57:27,744 --> 00:57:30,747
but you're saying Nam-no
has always remained on the other end.

1459
00:57:30,814 --> 00:57:32,615
Don't say it like that.

1460
00:57:32,682 --> 00:57:35,919
You know what?
I'm just pretending to be ugly.

1461
00:57:35,985 --> 00:57:37,987
-It was an act?
-You were pretending?

1462
00:57:38,054 --> 00:57:40,790
-You're acting.
-If I starve myself for a couple of days,

1463
00:57:40,857 --> 00:57:43,793
I think I can easily beat Sung-jun

1464
00:57:43,860 --> 00:57:46,129
-when it comes to looks.
-Easily?

1465
00:57:46,196 --> 00:57:50,633
He's the type
who overrates what he looks like.

1466
00:57:50,700 --> 00:57:54,671
-I have high self-esteem.
-He talks like he's on Jong-won's level…

1467
00:57:54,737 --> 00:57:57,674
-Don't drag me into it.
-…and I find it quite unpleasant.

1468
00:57:57,740 --> 00:57:59,242
Not the same. I'm a little lower.

1469
00:58:01,311 --> 00:58:03,313
PIZZA'S SELF-ESTEEM

1470
00:58:03,379 --> 00:58:07,016
Nam-no said this about Sung-jun.

1471
00:58:07,083 --> 00:58:08,084
About his looks.

1472
00:58:08,151 --> 00:58:11,888
"Sung-jun looks like
Poong's Chinese kitchen knife."

1473
00:58:11,955 --> 00:58:13,389
What does that even mean?

1474
00:58:13,456 --> 00:58:15,925
Why does it have to be mine?

1475
00:58:15,992 --> 00:58:18,094
HOW CAN A MAN
LOOK LIKE A CHINESE KITCHEN KNIFE?

1476
00:58:18,161 --> 00:58:20,196
I knew I oddly wanted to use him to chop.

1477
00:58:20,430 --> 00:58:21,598
DEFINITELY A CHINESE CHEF'S KNIFE

1478
00:58:21,664 --> 00:58:24,300
His face is square-shaped,
like a Chinese kitchen knife.

1479
00:58:24,367 --> 00:58:27,504
Because they both insist
that one looks better than the other,

1480
00:58:27,570 --> 00:58:29,439
we quickly held a secret ballot.

1481
00:58:29,506 --> 00:58:30,640
Wait.

1482
00:58:30,707 --> 00:58:33,309
We asked,
"Who embodies The Ugliness more?"

1483
00:58:35,612 --> 00:58:39,949
<i>We had 46 people,</i>
<i>including crew and cast members,</i>

1484
00:58:40,016 --> 00:58:42,652
<i>vote between Sung-jun and Nam-no,</i>

1485
00:58:42,719 --> 00:58:44,220
Why would you do this?

1486
00:58:44,287 --> 00:58:45,722
They're the same.

1487
00:58:48,491 --> 00:58:50,026
5 CHEFS AND POONG ALL VOTED

1488
00:58:50,093 --> 00:58:51,895
-And this is the result.
-Seriously?

1489
00:58:51,961 --> 00:58:53,129
It's a close match.

1490
00:58:53,196 --> 00:58:55,131
-A close match?
-It's a close match.

1491
00:58:55,398 --> 00:58:58,134
INTRIGUING

1492
00:58:58,201 --> 00:59:02,071
-One person abstained,
-Abstained? That's the worst.

1493
00:59:02,138 --> 00:59:03,806
The result of the survey

1494
00:59:03,873 --> 00:59:05,341
looks like this.

1495
00:59:05,642 --> 00:59:07,443
NAM-NO: 28 VS. SUNG-JUN: 17

1496
00:59:07,510 --> 00:59:09,045
Hey! I got more!

1497
00:59:09,112 --> 00:59:10,280
I won by a lot!

1498
00:59:10,346 --> 00:59:11,281
HEHEHE

1499
00:59:13,149 --> 00:59:15,585
You dummy.

1500
00:59:15,652 --> 00:59:17,921
NAM-NO… IT MEANS YOU'RE WORSE-LOOKING…

1501
00:59:17,987 --> 00:59:20,990
-Wait, I didn't win?
-Will you read what it says?

1502
00:59:21,057 --> 00:59:25,261
Read the topic
and figure out what it is first! Please!

1503
00:59:25,328 --> 00:59:27,130
-Nam-no!
-You're perfect.

1504
00:59:27,196 --> 00:59:28,831
You shouldn't be happy.

1505
00:59:28,898 --> 00:59:30,867
Wait, I need less votes to win.

1506
00:59:31,267 --> 00:59:33,903
OUR DEAR NAM-NO FINALLY UNDERSTOOD

1507
00:59:33,970 --> 00:59:36,306
-Well, in a way, he "won."
-Yes.

1508
00:59:36,372 --> 00:59:39,475
-After all, first place is great.
-Yes, he won.

1509
00:59:39,542 --> 00:59:41,344
Here are some comments from the voters.

1510
00:59:41,411 --> 00:59:43,913
"Sung-jun's features
are parked in the right places."

1511
00:59:43,980 --> 00:59:46,282
"They're in the dead center."

1512
00:59:46,349 --> 00:59:47,750
"There's lots of space,

1513
00:59:47,817 --> 00:59:49,886
so why were they
only parked in the center?"

1514
00:59:49,953 --> 00:59:51,287
I'll analyze the handwriting.

1515
00:59:51,354 --> 00:59:55,358
That was a comment from a chef
with the last name Son.

1516
00:59:55,425 --> 00:59:56,859
When you're at a highway rest stop,

1517
00:59:56,926 --> 00:59:58,528
you can sometimes see a sedan

1518
00:59:58,595 --> 01:00:01,397
parked in the space
that's meant for buses.

1519
01:00:01,698 --> 01:00:03,099
LOTS OF SPACE TO GO AROUND

1520
01:00:03,166 --> 01:00:06,803
"Sung-jun has defined features
and is quite good-looking."

1521
01:00:06,869 --> 01:00:08,504
"But he is pretty old-fashioned."

1522
01:00:08,805 --> 01:00:10,740
TRIGGERED

1523
01:00:10,807 --> 01:00:14,077
-An opinion from a certain Mr. Namkoong.
-What?

1524
01:00:14,143 --> 01:00:14,978
No idea who it is.

1525
01:00:15,044 --> 01:00:18,181
-I really don't know. Tell us!
-Someone with the surname Namkoong?

1526
01:00:18,548 --> 01:00:20,416
WOW, I CAN'T EVEN TAKE A GUESS…

1527
01:00:20,483 --> 01:00:22,652
-Who said that?
-A crew member.

1528
01:00:22,719 --> 01:00:23,987
Probably the camera operator.

1529
01:00:24,053 --> 01:00:25,588
I don't think it's me.

1530
01:00:25,655 --> 01:00:27,123
HAS NOTHING TO DO WITH ME

1531
01:00:27,190 --> 01:00:30,293
All of the chefs, including Poong,

1532
01:00:30,360 --> 01:00:32,528
voted for Sung-jun.

1533
01:00:32,595 --> 01:00:33,997
It was unanimous.

1534
01:00:34,063 --> 01:00:36,032
That's hilarious.

1535
01:00:36,099 --> 01:00:38,735
Let's say
you enjoyed the food so much today

1536
01:00:38,801 --> 01:00:41,004
that your face changed tomorrow.

1537
01:00:41,070 --> 01:00:43,072
Between them, who's face would you choose?

1538
01:00:43,139 --> 01:00:44,207
WHOSE FACE WILL IT BE?

1539
01:00:44,273 --> 01:00:46,442
-You loved the food.
-You enjoyed it so much.

1540
01:00:46,509 --> 01:00:47,644
-That much?
-You're bloated.

1541
01:00:47,710 --> 01:00:49,812
Yes, you didn't think of tomorrow.

1542
01:00:49,879 --> 01:00:51,114
-Who would you wake up as?
-I choose

1543
01:00:51,180 --> 01:00:53,716
-Chef Nam-no.
-Nam-no. It's Nam-no.

1544
01:00:53,783 --> 01:00:56,653
-I knew it.
-Wait. Did I win or lose?

1545
01:00:56,719 --> 01:00:57,787
-You won.
-You won this one.

1546
01:00:57,854 --> 01:00:59,322
-I won? For real?
-You did.

1547
01:00:59,389 --> 01:01:01,257
-That means you have Min's vibes.
-Yes.

1548
01:01:01,324 --> 01:01:03,559
His looks are a little more modern.

1549
01:01:03,626 --> 01:01:06,396
-He looks more modern.
-More modern.

1550
01:01:06,462 --> 01:01:07,697
He keeps mentioning

1551
01:01:07,764 --> 01:01:11,067
-modern and old-fashioned.
-What's a modern look supposed to be?

1552
01:01:11,134 --> 01:01:14,270
-Sung-jun is actually younger.
-It's not like that.

1553
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:18,207
He's the youngest here, but he keeps
getting calling old-fashioned.

1554
01:01:19,142 --> 01:01:21,310
CHEF NAM-NO'S INGREDIENTS:
PORK BELLY, EEL, GLASS NOODLES

1555
01:01:21,377 --> 01:01:23,212
RED WINE, RED CHILI PEPPER,
PICKLED GINGER SLICES

1556
01:01:23,279 --> 01:01:25,948
First up, Chef Nam-no.
What are you making?

1557
01:01:26,015 --> 01:01:27,784
My dish is called

1558
01:01:28,317 --> 01:01:30,753
Yoon Nam-No Handsome.

1559
01:01:30,820 --> 01:01:33,890
-No Handsome.
-Not handsome, so No Handsome.

1560
01:01:33,956 --> 01:01:35,858
What's the dish like?

1561
01:01:35,925 --> 01:01:36,893
That was lame.

1562
01:01:36,959 --> 01:01:38,995
Even someone handsome like Min

1563
01:01:39,062 --> 01:01:40,697
can eat this dish,

1564
01:01:40,763 --> 01:01:43,966
look in the mirror,
and let out the deepest sigh,

1565
01:01:44,033 --> 01:01:46,936
-because you'll be so bloated.
-It'll make him bloated?

1566
01:01:47,003 --> 01:01:51,140
I'll cook with the trio,
pork belly, eel, and green onion.

1567
01:01:51,207 --> 01:01:53,276
Pork belly, eel, and green onion.

1568
01:01:53,342 --> 01:01:55,378
-Sounds good.
-They don't have any carbs,

1569
01:01:55,445 --> 01:01:57,046
so I'll deep-fry lots of glass noodles

1570
01:01:57,113 --> 01:02:00,383
and make sure your blood sugar spikes.

1571
01:02:00,450 --> 01:02:02,719
-Pork belly and eel.
-Goodness.

1572
01:02:02,785 --> 01:02:05,054
-He'll make your face bloated.
-Yes.

1573
01:02:05,121 --> 01:02:06,489
Yoon Nam-No Handsome.

1574
01:02:07,323 --> 01:02:09,392
CHEF SUNG-JUN'S INGREDIENTS:
FREGULA, PORK BELLY, MANILA CLAM

1575
01:02:09,459 --> 01:02:11,494
BONE BROTH, ROASTED SWEET POTATO,
POTATO, ZUCCHINI, AND MORE

1576
01:02:11,561 --> 01:02:13,429
The dish I'm making is

1577
01:02:13,496 --> 01:02:14,831
Ugly Namkoong Min.

1578
01:02:14,897 --> 01:02:18,234
-Ugly Namkoong Min?
-Ugly Namkoong Min? Ugly?

1579
01:02:18,301 --> 01:02:20,269
-Ugly?
-Are you calling him ugly?

1580
01:02:20,336 --> 01:02:22,105
He called you ugly.

1581
01:02:22,171 --> 01:02:24,307
-He could feel offended.
-Is this your revenge?

1582
01:02:24,373 --> 01:02:26,809
Is this revenge
for him calling you old-fashioned?

1583
01:02:26,876 --> 01:02:29,545
-Looking old-fashioned.
-I'm sorry.

1584
01:02:29,612 --> 01:02:31,514
You've never been called ugly, right?

1585
01:02:31,581 --> 01:02:34,117
But it rolls right off the tongue.

1586
01:02:34,183 --> 01:02:37,420
The words ugly, Namkoong, and Min

1587
01:02:37,487 --> 01:02:39,222
all flow like one phrase.

1588
01:02:39,288 --> 01:02:43,760
-Ugly Namkoong Min. It works.
-I see.

1589
01:02:43,826 --> 01:02:45,561
He looks great now,

1590
01:02:45,628 --> 01:02:48,498
but I'll make something that'll turn him
into Ugly Namkoong Min by tomorrow.

1591
01:02:48,564 --> 01:02:50,032
That was what I meant.

1592
01:02:50,099 --> 01:02:53,169
I'm also the type
that gets bloated the moment I eat,

1593
01:02:53,236 --> 01:02:54,504
and my secret

1594
01:02:54,570 --> 01:02:57,774
is salty broth.
I always need some kind of soup.

1595
01:02:57,840 --> 01:02:59,208
And then, something sweet.

1596
01:02:59,275 --> 01:03:02,512
-Yes. Right.
-I alternate between sweet and salty

1597
01:03:02,578 --> 01:03:03,713
to look like this the next day.

1598
01:03:03,780 --> 01:03:06,549
I'll make you have well-parked features
with a <i>sujebi</i>-like face.

1599
01:03:06,616 --> 01:03:08,584
-Yes.
-You can be reborn as ugly.

1600
01:03:08,651 --> 01:03:10,486
-That's true.
-So I'll prepare that today.

1601
01:03:10,553 --> 01:03:12,155
I'll use pork belly

1602
01:03:12,221 --> 01:03:14,590
to make pasta inspired by <i>doenjang-jjigae</i>.

1603
01:03:15,758 --> 01:03:19,428
You had grain-shaped pasta called <i>fregula</i>,

1604
01:03:19,495 --> 01:03:22,031
so I'll make it like <i>doenjang-sulbap.</i>

1605
01:03:22,098 --> 01:03:24,667
Also, it seemed like
you often ate sweet potatoes

1606
01:03:24,734 --> 01:03:26,035
-to stay in shape.
-Yes.

1607
01:03:26,102 --> 01:03:29,605
I'll turn that into crème brûlée

1608
01:03:29,672 --> 01:03:32,642
with almond milk and eggs.

1609
01:03:32,708 --> 01:03:35,711
-The sweet and salty mix.
-The sweet and salty mix.

1610
01:03:35,778 --> 01:03:38,114
-The winner today…
-The worst-looking one.

1611
01:03:38,181 --> 01:03:40,349
…is the less good-looking one.

1612
01:03:40,416 --> 01:03:43,186
Let us begin the next round, The Ugliness.

1613
01:03:43,252 --> 01:03:44,887
Hey.

1614
01:03:45,588 --> 01:03:47,323
They look cool in the dark.

1615
01:03:48,157 --> 01:03:50,393
EVEN COOLER WHEN IT'S COMPLETELY DARK

1616
01:03:50,459 --> 01:03:52,595
-Much better.
-He's feeling the light.

1617
01:03:52,662 --> 01:03:54,397
He looks great under the light.

1618
01:03:54,463 --> 01:03:56,098
UNBELIEVABLE

1619
01:03:56,165 --> 01:03:57,667
Nam-no, lift your face up too.

1620
01:03:58,167 --> 01:04:00,069
More. Higher.

1621
01:04:00,136 --> 01:04:01,170
POONG TEACHES HIM HOW TO LOOK BETTER

1622
01:04:01,537 --> 01:04:03,406
YOU CAN LEARN FROM ME

1623
01:04:04,607 --> 01:04:05,675
He's trying to look cool.

1624
01:04:05,741 --> 01:04:07,109
He reminds me of Moai.

1625
01:04:08,311 --> 01:04:09,745
MOAI LOOKS TACKY…

1626
01:04:09,812 --> 01:04:11,914
He looks more like one
because his face is square-shaped.

1627
01:04:11,981 --> 01:04:15,952
Here to park Min's features
in all the wrong places today,

1628
01:04:16,018 --> 01:04:18,221
Chef Kwon Sung-jun.

1629
01:04:18,287 --> 01:04:20,389
A man who doesn't need to understand
the topic today

1630
01:04:20,456 --> 01:04:22,692
because it's already his whole existence…

1631
01:04:22,758 --> 01:04:25,494
-His existence?
-…Chef Yoon Nam-no.

1632
01:04:25,561 --> 01:04:28,698
Who will rise as the winner
and complete his ugliness?

1633
01:04:28,764 --> 01:04:32,001
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1634
01:04:32,935 --> 01:04:34,937
PERFECT THE UGLINESS!

1635
01:04:36,672 --> 01:04:37,840
ALMOND MILK

1636
01:04:37,907 --> 01:04:39,475
I'm so excited about this.

1637
01:04:39,542 --> 01:04:42,678
-The ugliness neck-and-neck fight.
-Sung-jun understood it right

1638
01:04:42,745 --> 01:04:44,513
because water is the key
to getting bloated.

1639
01:04:44,580 --> 01:04:45,448
Yes.

1640
01:04:45,514 --> 01:04:47,416
Because he's making
something salty with soup,

1641
01:04:47,483 --> 01:04:49,852
he might have a better chance.

1642
01:04:49,919 --> 01:04:52,221
-Well, in theory.
-Yes.

1643
01:04:52,288 --> 01:04:56,525
I think Chef Nam-no
should make something with soup too.

1644
01:04:56,592 --> 01:04:57,894
Eel and pork.

1645
01:04:57,960 --> 01:05:00,229
-He's slipping garlic into the pork.
-Garlic.

1646
01:05:00,296 --> 01:05:02,231
If he puts garlic in the meat…

1647
01:05:02,298 --> 01:05:04,033
-Will it get cooked?
-It'll take a while.

1648
01:05:04,100 --> 01:05:05,167
It won't get cooked.

1649
01:05:05,234 --> 01:05:07,203
-It won't? Then why are you doing that?
-It won't.

1650
01:05:07,270 --> 01:05:08,537
-For the scent.
-Oh, the scent.

1651
01:05:08,604 --> 01:05:10,973
We also eat raw garlic, anyway.

1652
01:05:11,040 --> 01:05:14,243
I've never seen anyone
slip garlic into pork before.

1653
01:05:14,310 --> 01:05:16,112
Sweet potato.

1654
01:05:16,178 --> 01:05:17,713
Sweet potato? When did he roast it?

1655
01:05:17,780 --> 01:05:20,549
-He had it.
-It was from his meal boxes.

1656
01:05:20,616 --> 01:05:22,418
-He had them in the salad.
-You're right.

1657
01:05:23,286 --> 01:05:24,153
CHOP ONE SWEET POTATO

1658
01:05:24,220 --> 01:05:26,956
Did you just throw
some pieces of sweet potato in the milk?

1659
01:05:27,023 --> 01:05:29,392
Yes, it's almond milk.

1660
01:05:29,458 --> 01:05:30,426
Almond milk, I see.

1661
01:05:30,493 --> 01:05:32,428
-I see.
-Back in my day,

1662
01:05:32,495 --> 01:05:34,697
potatoes were often used
to describe bad-looking people.

1663
01:05:34,764 --> 01:05:36,332
-Yes, right.
-Yes, potatoes.

1664
01:05:36,399 --> 01:05:38,734
-Like how we use squid now.
-Yes, people use squid.

1665
01:05:38,801 --> 01:05:40,069
It went from potato to squid.

1666
01:05:40,136 --> 01:05:42,405
Long ago, Eul-yong was called Potato.

1667
01:05:42,805 --> 01:05:43,706
A SUDDEN DISS TOWARD HIS FRIEND

1668
01:05:43,940 --> 01:05:45,341
I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M A POTATO!

1669
01:05:45,408 --> 01:05:46,242
TAP!

1670
01:05:47,410 --> 01:05:48,244
TAP!

1671
01:05:49,478 --> 01:05:50,313
TAP!

1672
01:05:50,379 --> 01:05:51,714
ONION

1673
01:05:52,114 --> 01:05:54,383
2. CHOP PORK, POTATO, AND ONION,
THEN STIR-FRY

1674
01:05:55,318 --> 01:05:57,553
Will he deep-fry that? No, pan fry.

1675
01:05:57,620 --> 01:06:00,423
Nam-no pan-fries the pork belly

1676
01:06:00,489 --> 01:06:02,525
after coating them slightly in flour.

1677
01:06:02,591 --> 01:06:03,793
2. PANFRY PORK WITH GREEN ONION

1678
01:06:05,461 --> 01:06:06,729
He grabs the eel.

1679
01:06:07,363 --> 01:06:08,831
Nam-no grabs the eel.

1680
01:06:08,898 --> 01:06:10,766
-Are you making cuts?
-He's making cuts.

1681
01:06:10,833 --> 01:06:12,468
Those cuts will help the eel

1682
01:06:12,535 --> 01:06:15,271
absorb the sauce inside and remain flat.

1683
01:06:15,338 --> 01:06:17,306
It won't curl up?

1684
01:06:17,373 --> 01:06:19,208
He's making shallow cuts in the eel.

1685
01:06:19,275 --> 01:06:20,543
Shallow cuts.

1686
01:06:20,609 --> 01:06:22,144
Both horizontal and vertical cuts.

1687
01:06:23,713 --> 01:06:27,450
3. GRILL EEL WITH A PRESSING PLATE

1688
01:06:27,516 --> 01:06:30,486
Chef Sung-jun is using lots of vegetables.

1689
01:06:30,553 --> 01:06:33,289
-That'll make him healthy and handsome.
-It looks healthy.

1690
01:06:33,356 --> 01:06:34,256
You're right.

1691
01:06:34,323 --> 01:06:36,525
-No, it's for the flavor.
-For the flavor?

1692
01:06:36,826 --> 01:06:38,160
EAT TOO MUCH AND YOU'LL BE UGLY

1693
01:06:38,494 --> 01:06:39,328
CRUSHED GARLIC

1694
01:06:39,795 --> 01:06:42,465
FIRST AND FOREMOST,
THE DOENJANG-JJIGAE MUST BE GOOD!

1695
01:06:43,699 --> 01:06:44,767
Are those Venus clams?

1696
01:06:44,834 --> 01:06:46,268
-Manila clams.
-Manila clams.

1697
01:06:46,335 --> 01:06:48,304
-Manila clams.
-They're huge.

1698
01:06:48,371 --> 01:06:50,439
There's a bigger kind.

1699
01:06:50,506 --> 01:06:52,108
PORK & MANILA CLAM DOENJANG-JJIGAE!

1700
01:06:52,174 --> 01:06:53,342
-Zucchini.
-Zucchini?

1701
01:06:53,409 --> 01:06:56,512
-He's using so many healthy ingredients.
-It seems healthy.

1702
01:06:56,579 --> 01:06:57,913
OYSTER MUSHROOM

1703
01:06:57,980 --> 01:07:01,250
I hope it's not regular <i>doenjang-jjigae</i>
made with some pasta.

1704
01:07:01,317 --> 01:07:03,652
-No way.
-He wouldn't do that.

1705
01:07:03,719 --> 01:07:05,621
-He's a creative one!
-Yes.

1706
01:07:05,688 --> 01:07:07,123
He strives to be creative.

1707
01:07:07,189 --> 01:07:08,290
Yes, that can't be right.

1708
01:07:08,524 --> 01:07:10,059
LOVING IT♥

1709
01:07:10,526 --> 01:07:11,694
4. ADD DOENJANG, GOCHUJANG, AND BOIL

1710
01:07:11,761 --> 01:07:14,663
-Are you adding <i>doenjang</i>?
-I am.

1711
01:07:14,730 --> 01:07:17,833
-Is the <i>doenjang </i>homemade? The color…
-It must be.

1712
01:07:18,067 --> 01:07:19,268
CHECKS THE LABEL

1713
01:07:19,335 --> 01:07:21,003
-Fermented for five years.
-For five years.

1714
01:07:21,771 --> 01:07:22,805
You had that at home.

1715
01:07:23,439 --> 01:07:26,642
You had <i>doenjang</i> that had been
fermented for five years at home.

1716
01:07:26,709 --> 01:07:28,511
He's adding the pasta.

1717
01:07:28,577 --> 01:07:32,281
-He's adding pasta to the <i>doenjang-jjigae.</i>
-Yes, that's what he's doing.

1718
01:07:32,348 --> 01:07:34,450
Were those peas or pasta?

1719
01:07:34,517 --> 01:07:36,085
-That's pasta?
-Yes.

1720
01:07:36,385 --> 01:07:37,753
NAM-NO MAKES THE BRAISING SAUCE

1721
01:07:38,020 --> 01:07:42,558
4. MIX CRUSHED GINGER, SOY SAUCE, SUGAR,
COOKING WINE, AND WATER FOR THE SAUCE

1722
01:07:43,492 --> 01:07:45,795
GRILLED GREEN ONION
LEAVES THE PAN FOR A MOMENT

1723
01:07:46,996 --> 01:07:47,963
RED WINE

1724
01:07:49,198 --> 01:07:51,700
MAKE HIM EVEN UGLIER!

1725
01:07:52,501 --> 01:07:53,669
You're doing something cool?

1726
01:07:54,136 --> 01:07:55,805
THAT WAS COOL, NAM-NO

1727
01:07:55,871 --> 01:07:58,507
You two look so cool when you cook, but…

1728
01:07:58,574 --> 01:07:59,809
MAINTAINING HIS CHARACTER

1729
01:08:00,309 --> 01:08:01,911
UNCOVER THE EEL

1730
01:08:04,080 --> 01:08:05,481
Chopping the onion.

1731
01:08:06,749 --> 01:08:09,452
-Red chili pepper, sliced.
-Yes, red chili pepper slices.

1732
01:08:09,518 --> 01:08:10,619
Hey, even his knife

1733
01:08:10,686 --> 01:08:12,488
is chubby and short.

1734
01:08:13,022 --> 01:08:14,490
CONFIRMING!

1735
01:08:15,091 --> 01:08:16,225
Why am I like this today?

1736
01:08:16,492 --> 01:08:17,927
THE AFTERMATH OF WRITING NICE COMMENTS?

1737
01:08:17,993 --> 01:08:19,895
He's full of spite today.

1738
01:08:19,962 --> 01:08:21,397
He's like a poisonous frog.

1739
01:08:21,697 --> 01:08:23,933
ADD THE SOY-BASED SAUCE!

1740
01:08:24,834 --> 01:08:25,668
ONION

1741
01:08:26,836 --> 01:08:27,670
EEL

1742
01:08:27,937 --> 01:08:28,771
GRILLED GREEN ONION

1743
01:08:29,905 --> 01:08:33,275
You have under ten minutes left.
Ten minutes!

1744
01:08:34,543 --> 01:08:36,579
He's making crème brûlée.

1745
01:08:36,645 --> 01:08:38,981
But you aren't using the yolks?

1746
01:08:39,048 --> 01:08:40,983
You need them to make it.

1747
01:08:41,050 --> 01:08:43,953
I'm making both crème brûlée
and sesame tuile.

1748
01:08:44,019 --> 01:08:45,988
-Sesame tuile.
-Sesame tuile?

1749
01:08:46,055 --> 01:08:47,189
-Tuile.
-Sesame.

1750
01:08:47,256 --> 01:08:49,158
-Tuile.
-Made with sesame.

1751
01:08:51,560 --> 01:08:52,661
I see.

1752
01:08:52,728 --> 01:08:54,363
So that is advantageous.

1753
01:08:54,430 --> 01:08:57,967
He can whisk much faster
because his limbs are shorter.

1754
01:08:58,033 --> 01:08:59,535
BECAUSE OF THE SHORTER RADIUS?

1755
01:08:59,602 --> 01:09:01,871
Why are you so spiteful today?

1756
01:09:01,937 --> 01:09:04,140
-You're that guy today.
-It's not like you are

1757
01:09:04,206 --> 01:09:06,442
-a poisonous toad.
-You keep attacking junior chefs.

1758
01:09:06,509 --> 01:09:10,246
I'm always on the other end,
so I wanted to try reversing that today.

1759
01:09:10,312 --> 01:09:11,580
You're mean, Grandpa.

1760
01:09:13,149 --> 01:09:15,851
6. MIX EGG WHITES, SUGAR, FLOUR, BUTTER,
BLACK SESAME, AND SESAME

1761
01:09:15,918 --> 01:09:18,320
-Tuile. He said he'd make sesame tuile.
-Just like that?

1762
01:09:18,387 --> 01:09:20,089
You're pouring it on a tray?

1763
01:09:20,156 --> 01:09:23,025
-I think he'll throw it in the oven.
-In the oven?

1764
01:09:23,092 --> 01:09:25,227
He has about ten minutes now.

1765
01:09:25,294 --> 01:09:26,328
It has to be thin.

1766
01:09:26,395 --> 01:09:27,897
It's like a piece of art.

1767
01:09:27,963 --> 01:09:31,066
-It's like flooring.
-That's a popular style now.

1768
01:09:31,133 --> 01:09:33,169
They remind me of frog eggs.

1769
01:09:33,235 --> 01:09:35,304
Or even leopard print.

1770
01:09:37,306 --> 01:09:38,974
He threw in glass noodles.

1771
01:09:39,041 --> 01:09:41,010
SURPRISE!

1772
01:09:41,076 --> 01:09:42,845
What's that? Glass noodles?

1773
01:09:42,912 --> 01:09:44,813
-That happens when fried.
-It's like art.

1774
01:09:44,880 --> 01:09:45,714
Hey, hey.

1775
01:09:45,781 --> 01:09:47,249
That was an unexpected performance.

1776
01:09:47,316 --> 01:09:48,684
That was great.

1777
01:09:48,751 --> 01:09:50,119
Whose hair is that?

1778
01:09:50,185 --> 01:09:53,155
-Nam-no's.
-It's so ugly!

1779
01:09:53,222 --> 01:09:55,024
AS EXPECTED, THE FINAL FORM OF BEAUTY

1780
01:09:56,692 --> 01:09:59,061
A CARB BOMB

1781
01:09:59,995 --> 01:10:02,231
That is a lot.

1782
01:10:02,298 --> 01:10:04,533
-You can use it as a wig too.
-Yes.

1783
01:10:04,600 --> 01:10:06,268
What will he do with that?

1784
01:10:07,703 --> 01:10:09,972
His <i>doenjang-jjigae</i> already looks good.

1785
01:10:10,039 --> 01:10:12,274
But will it go well with pasta?

1786
01:10:12,341 --> 01:10:14,143
I'll make it a bit saltier.

1787
01:10:14,210 --> 01:10:16,579
He adds bone broth to add depth.

1788
01:10:16,645 --> 01:10:17,479
It looks good.

1789
01:10:18,747 --> 01:10:21,083
-MSG?
-He's using MSG.

1790
01:10:21,150 --> 01:10:24,186
-These chefs are using MSG freely.
-All these chefs

1791
01:10:24,253 --> 01:10:27,122
are using MSG out in the open.

1792
01:10:27,189 --> 01:10:28,691
I ruined all of them!

1793
01:10:28,757 --> 01:10:30,025
You did.

1794
01:10:30,092 --> 01:10:33,128
-Before, they used to be secretive.
-They did it in secret,

1795
01:10:33,195 --> 01:10:36,999
then had to go pray on the weekends
because they felt guilty.

1796
01:10:37,066 --> 01:10:39,668
After Sam used <i>ramyeon</i> soup base,

1797
01:10:39,735 --> 01:10:42,004
-he went on a pilgrimage.
-Yes, I'm telling you.

1798
01:10:42,805 --> 01:10:45,274
Sung-jun's <i>doenjang-jjigae.</i>

1799
01:10:45,341 --> 01:10:48,043
He tastes it once again.

1800
01:10:48,110 --> 01:10:49,812
-Is it too salty?
-It's fine.

1801
01:10:49,878 --> 01:10:51,780
"It's fine."

1802
01:10:51,847 --> 01:10:54,149
It needs to be tasty too,
not just salty to make him bloated.

1803
01:10:54,216 --> 01:10:55,684
-Of course.
-Right.

1804
01:10:55,751 --> 01:10:57,219
Why are you adding water?

1805
01:10:57,286 --> 01:10:58,854
Yes, you said it was fine.

1806
01:10:58,921 --> 01:11:01,924
-You added a huge amount of it.
-That was so much water.

1807
01:11:01,991 --> 01:11:03,225
Might as well make a new batch.

1808
01:11:03,292 --> 01:11:05,661
No, it tastes perfect.

1809
01:11:05,728 --> 01:11:08,631
-Isn't it better to start over?
-That could feed so many people.

1810
01:11:08,697 --> 01:11:14,069
Nam-no's pork also seems salty.

1811
01:11:14,136 --> 01:11:16,105
It looks great.

1812
01:11:16,505 --> 01:11:18,240
BOILED SWEET POTATO & ALMOND MILK

1813
01:11:19,308 --> 01:11:21,610
-What's that? What's he blending?
-Sweet potato, I think.

1814
01:11:21,677 --> 01:11:23,846
-The one in almond milk?
-Is he blending sweet potato?

1815
01:11:24,413 --> 01:11:25,714
GULP

1816
01:11:26,181 --> 01:11:27,416
What's that for?

1817
01:11:27,483 --> 01:11:30,219
-It's the dessert.
-He's making crème brûlée.

1818
01:11:30,286 --> 01:11:33,022
It has to harden, so he added egg yolks.

1819
01:11:33,088 --> 01:11:35,557
It can turn out like steamed eggs.

1820
01:11:35,624 --> 01:11:36,592
KEPT COLD IN THE FREEZER

1821
01:11:36,659 --> 01:11:38,827
That'll take a while, then.

1822
01:11:38,894 --> 01:11:42,531
Five minutes!
Jung-hwan, please report from the kitchen.

1823
01:11:42,598 --> 01:11:45,834
The ugly looks match.
Who'll make Min uglier?

1824
01:11:45,901 --> 01:11:47,903
Yes, hurry over.

1825
01:11:47,970 --> 01:11:50,239
-Hurrying.
-And try Sung-jun's <i>jjigae</i>.

1826
01:11:50,939 --> 01:11:53,542
It's made with <i>doenjang</i>
that has been fermented for five years.

1827
01:11:53,609 --> 01:11:56,845
Scoop up a spoon and try it!

1828
01:11:56,912 --> 01:11:58,814
How's Sung-jun's <i>doenjang-jjigae</i>?

1829
01:11:58,881 --> 01:12:01,684
Does it taste good enough
to make Ugly Namkoong Min?

1830
01:12:03,585 --> 01:12:06,789
I don't think he'll become
Ugly Namkoong Min at the moment.

1831
01:12:06,855 --> 01:12:08,457
It's unexpectedly bland, actually.

1832
01:12:08,524 --> 01:12:10,426
-Gosh.
-He added too much water earlier.

1833
01:12:10,492 --> 01:12:11,760
It has to boil down.

1834
01:12:11,827 --> 01:12:13,429
-You have four minutes.
-Four minutes.

1835
01:12:13,495 --> 01:12:16,065
It's how I usually eat,

1836
01:12:16,131 --> 01:12:17,566
which means it's not salty.

1837
01:12:17,633 --> 01:12:19,234
Jung-hwan, can you go next door

1838
01:12:19,301 --> 01:12:21,270
and check out Nam-no's pork?

1839
01:12:21,337 --> 01:12:24,673
-Try the sauce it's boiling in.
-The sauce.

1840
01:12:24,740 --> 01:12:29,011
That sauce. Will it turn Min
into a "no handsome" guy?

1841
01:12:30,913 --> 01:12:32,715
Yes, he'll become a "no handsome" guy.

1842
01:12:32,781 --> 01:12:34,750
Is it salty?

1843
01:12:34,817 --> 01:12:36,151
Yes, salty and rich.

1844
01:12:37,086 --> 01:12:39,722
It has both sweetness and saltiness.

1845
01:12:39,788 --> 01:12:40,989
Yes, you need both.

1846
01:12:41,056 --> 01:12:43,826
-It's going on a gridiron.
-A gridiron?

1847
01:12:43,892 --> 01:12:46,095
He boiled the pork in the sauce,
and is grilling it this time.

1848
01:12:46,161 --> 01:12:47,730
Hey, great job, Iberico piggy!

1849
01:12:47,796 --> 01:12:49,231
He's definitely good.

1850
01:12:49,298 --> 01:12:52,868
-That's delicious.
-That's Ho-young's go-to method.

1851
01:12:52,935 --> 01:12:55,404
-It's good.
-Yes, that's Ho-young's thing.

1852
01:12:55,471 --> 01:12:56,739
And the eel too.

1853
01:12:56,805 --> 01:12:59,541
Nam-no came ready today.

1854
01:12:59,608 --> 01:13:02,211
He's already plating the food.

1855
01:13:02,277 --> 01:13:03,746
OPEN!

1856
01:13:03,812 --> 01:13:05,514
What's that, Sung-jun?

1857
01:13:05,581 --> 01:13:06,982
-Sweet potato?
-Roasted.

1858
01:13:07,049 --> 01:13:09,351
-Sweet potato?
-I've warmed it up in the air fryer.

1859
01:13:09,418 --> 01:13:10,486
He warmed it up.

1860
01:13:10,552 --> 01:13:12,020
-He did?
-It's on fire.

1861
01:13:12,087 --> 01:13:13,322
-Fire.
-It caught fire?

1862
01:13:14,289 --> 01:13:16,558
-It burns rapidly.
-Yes.

1863
01:13:16,625 --> 01:13:19,128
Something smells slightly burnt.

1864
01:13:19,194 --> 01:13:21,296
-Hey.
-I hope you cut that part out.

1865
01:13:21,363 --> 01:13:23,499
He's braising this once again.

1866
01:13:23,565 --> 01:13:26,635
He grilled it over a gridiron,
and then braises it once again.

1867
01:13:26,702 --> 01:13:31,340
And now, he's topping
fried glass noodles with ingredients.

1868
01:13:31,407 --> 01:13:33,075
Two minutes.

1869
01:13:33,142 --> 01:13:34,710
-Doesn't time fly?
-Yes.

1870
01:13:34,777 --> 01:13:37,913
Will this <i>doenjang-jjigae</i>
taste a little stronger now?

1871
01:13:37,980 --> 01:13:40,616
-Some time has passed.
-Two minutes left.

1872
01:13:40,682 --> 01:13:42,851
-Two minutes have passed.
-Two minutes.

1873
01:13:42,918 --> 01:13:44,386
-Let me check.
-It was bland before.

1874
01:13:44,453 --> 01:13:48,724
This time, does it taste like
it can make Ugly Namkoong Min?

1875
01:13:48,791 --> 01:13:52,127
-He'll be the ugliest in Korea!
-The ugliest in Korea?

1876
01:13:52,194 --> 01:13:53,829
It's definitely saltier.

1877
01:13:53,896 --> 01:13:55,864
-Quite strong.
-So it has boiled down.

1878
01:13:55,931 --> 01:13:57,666
When you eat <i>doenjang-sulbap,</i>

1879
01:13:57,733 --> 01:13:59,902
it tastes this salty
after the entire soup has boiled down.

1880
01:13:59,968 --> 01:14:01,303
-Yes.
-It's like that.

1881
01:14:01,370 --> 01:14:02,204
Yes, toward the end.

1882
01:14:02,271 --> 01:14:05,707
He has two more minutes,
which means he can boil it down more.

1883
01:14:05,774 --> 01:14:07,943
You may not wake up tomorrow.

1884
01:14:08,210 --> 01:14:09,545
THAT'S WHAT I WANT!

1885
01:14:10,112 --> 01:14:12,848
-Is the pasta cooked?
-Sung-jun scoops it out.

1886
01:14:12,915 --> 01:14:13,816
It's al dente.

1887
01:14:13,882 --> 01:14:15,384
-Al dente.
-Al dente.

1888
01:14:15,451 --> 01:14:19,188
The two have their looks on the line.
Who's going to win this?

1889
01:14:19,922 --> 01:14:20,856
-What's that?
-The sauce.

1890
01:14:20,923 --> 01:14:22,024
NAM-NO'S BRAISED DISH IS DONE TOO

1891
01:14:22,090 --> 01:14:23,959
-He pulls the meat out.
-It looks so good.

1892
01:14:24,026 --> 01:14:26,061
He's putting a lot of work
into the meat and the eel.

1893
01:14:26,128 --> 01:14:28,063
It looks so lustrous.

1894
01:14:28,130 --> 01:14:30,566
-The sauce.
-Just like that?

1895
01:14:30,632 --> 01:14:32,234
He's pouring the sauce there too.

1896
01:14:32,301 --> 01:14:34,436
-He can eat the glass noodles.
-That's true.

1897
01:14:34,503 --> 01:14:37,506
Then the noodles will wilt

1898
01:14:37,573 --> 01:14:39,074
-And turn soggy.
-and become soft.

1899
01:14:39,141 --> 01:14:40,509
One minute left.

1900
01:14:40,576 --> 01:14:43,378
-You have one minute left!
-One minute.

1901
01:14:43,445 --> 01:14:44,513
Start plating now.

1902
01:14:44,580 --> 01:14:47,282
You have to finish up. One minute left.

1903
01:14:47,349 --> 01:14:49,685
Yoon Nam-No Handsome
and Ugly Namkoong Min!

1904
01:14:50,919 --> 01:14:52,521
The tuile. Sesame tuile.

1905
01:14:52,588 --> 01:14:53,922
It's still in the making.

1906
01:14:53,989 --> 01:14:54,990
But you have no time.

1907
01:14:55,057 --> 01:14:56,225
You're right.

1908
01:14:56,291 --> 01:14:58,293
-You don't have time.
-Forty seconds.

1909
01:14:59,495 --> 01:15:00,429
OH! IT'S TOO HOT

1910
01:15:00,496 --> 01:15:03,098
-It must be hot.
-It's still too hot.

1911
01:15:03,165 --> 01:15:04,867
It's too hot!

1912
01:15:04,933 --> 01:15:07,369
So he's putting everything on top.
Thirty seconds!

1913
01:15:07,436 --> 01:15:08,971
-Thirty seconds!
-Thirty seconds!

1914
01:15:09,037 --> 01:15:12,140
-Thirty seconds.
-Make your dessert quickly.

1915
01:15:12,207 --> 01:15:13,408
-Wait.
-He's busy!

1916
01:15:13,475 --> 01:15:14,810
-Hurry!
-The torch is gone.

1917
01:15:14,877 --> 01:15:17,212
The torch? It's over here.

1918
01:15:17,446 --> 01:15:18,981
HANDSOME AT HEART

1919
01:15:19,047 --> 01:15:21,350
-Sugar.
-Did you get the tuile?

1920
01:15:21,416 --> 01:15:23,285
-Twenty seconds, Nam-no.
-You must hurry,

1921
01:15:23,352 --> 01:15:25,320
-even if it's too hot, Nam-no!
-It's too hot!

1922
01:15:25,387 --> 01:15:28,490
-Melt it with a torch!
-A torch!

1923
01:15:28,557 --> 01:15:31,860
-Let him break the top.
-Nam-no is done.

1924
01:15:32,394 --> 01:15:36,999
11. CARAMELIZE SUGAR
AND FINISH THE CRÈME BRÛLÉE

1925
01:15:37,199 --> 01:15:38,433
WOW

1926
01:15:38,500 --> 01:15:42,137
-Four. Three. Two. One.
-Three. Two. One.

1927
01:15:42,204 --> 01:15:43,305
Ding.

1928
01:15:43,372 --> 01:15:45,374
It's over. Time's up.

1929
01:15:45,641 --> 01:15:47,442
FINISHED THE CRÈME BRÛLÉE

1930
01:15:47,676 --> 01:15:50,679
IN THE END,
HE COULDN'T SERVE THE SESAME TUILE…

1931
01:15:52,080 --> 01:15:53,682
Wow.

1932
01:15:53,749 --> 01:15:56,018
Put it on the tray.

1933
01:15:56,084 --> 01:15:58,153
CANNOT SERVE
THE SESAME TUILE HE WORKED HARD ON

1934
01:15:58,620 --> 01:16:01,523
NOW! LET'S SEE HOW MUCH UGLIER HE BECOMES

1935
01:16:01,590 --> 01:16:03,859
This one looks really good, Min.

1936
01:16:03,926 --> 01:16:04,760
PHOTO FOR KEEPS

1937
01:16:05,561 --> 01:16:11,199
Both dishes were finished
for Min's round, The Ugliness.

1938
01:16:11,266 --> 01:16:13,769
-But the food looks pretty.
-They do.

1939
01:16:13,835 --> 01:16:16,038
I overheard him say,

1940
01:16:16,104 --> 01:16:19,508
"Not only do I like their dishes,

1941
01:16:19,575 --> 01:16:21,710
but I love the names."

1942
01:16:21,777 --> 01:16:25,781
If you say it together,
it's No Handsome, Ugly Namkoong Min.

1943
01:16:25,847 --> 01:16:29,084
-No Handsome, Ugly Namkoong Min?
-No Handsome, Ugly Namkoong Min?

1944
01:16:29,151 --> 01:16:31,954
It's like a series of attacks,
so it feels wonderful.

1945
01:16:32,020 --> 01:16:33,589
BWAHAHAHAHA!

1946
01:16:33,655 --> 01:16:36,058
When would you ever
hear anything like that?

1947
01:16:36,124 --> 01:16:37,526
Let's start in the order they finished.

1948
01:16:37,593 --> 01:16:39,995
-Chef Nam-no.
-Chef Nam-no's Yoon Nam-No Handsome.

1949
01:16:40,062 --> 01:16:46,835
PORK BELLY, EEL, AND GREEN ONION
SERVED ON FRIED GLASS NOODLES

1950
01:16:47,369 --> 01:16:51,506
CHEF YOON NAM-NO'S YOON NAM-NO HANDSOME

1951
01:16:52,274 --> 01:16:53,742
WELCOMING HIS NO HANDSOME DISH

1952
01:16:53,809 --> 01:16:55,077
I forgot

1953
01:16:55,143 --> 01:16:57,913
to top it with pickled chili peppers.

1954
01:16:57,980 --> 01:16:59,615
-Huh?
-So can we both…

1955
01:16:59,681 --> 01:17:01,617
I also couldn't use my sesame tuile.

1956
01:17:01,683 --> 01:17:03,552
May we both add one more thing?

1957
01:17:03,619 --> 01:17:05,253
Did you make pickled chili peppers?

1958
01:17:05,320 --> 01:17:08,790
-No, it's delicious store-bought…
-Store-bought?

1959
01:17:08,857 --> 01:17:10,559
I don't think it's necessary.

1960
01:17:10,626 --> 01:17:13,528
The two ugly guys can figure it out then.

1961
01:17:13,595 --> 01:17:15,731
-They both missed one.
-One each.

1962
01:17:15,797 --> 01:17:16,999
The sesame tuile is too strong.

1963
01:17:17,265 --> 01:17:18,900
LOOKING DELICIOUS

1964
01:17:18,967 --> 01:17:22,604
Don't let him do it.
The sesame tuile looks too good.

1965
01:17:22,671 --> 01:17:24,039
At least we're pretty at heart, right?

1966
01:17:25,240 --> 01:17:27,676
I'll give up on mine.

1967
01:17:29,311 --> 01:17:31,079
You're even ugly at heart!

1968
01:17:31,146 --> 01:17:32,814
All of a sudden?

1969
01:17:32,881 --> 01:17:34,116
You said you'd do it.

1970
01:17:34,182 --> 01:17:37,019
You're even ugly at heart!

1971
01:17:37,085 --> 01:17:38,920
Yes, I'm even ugly at heart.

1972
01:17:38,987 --> 01:17:40,522
-Then this is it.
-Okay.

1973
01:17:40,589 --> 01:17:43,759
First, this pork belly.

1974
01:17:45,127 --> 01:17:47,496
He first tries just the pork belly.

1975
01:17:47,996 --> 01:17:50,732
-He braised and grilled those.
-And grilled.

1976
01:17:50,799 --> 01:17:52,401
-And braised again.
-Yes.

1977
01:17:52,467 --> 01:17:55,504
He looks serious,

1978
01:17:55,570 --> 01:17:57,305
and he looked at Nam-no.

1979
01:17:57,372 --> 01:17:59,675
Because his decision

1980
01:17:59,741 --> 01:18:02,244
will decide the ugliest person.

1981
01:18:02,310 --> 01:18:05,814
-Something is seriously wrong.
-He glared at him once.

1982
01:18:05,881 --> 01:18:07,516
-It's not that.
-No?

1983
01:18:07,582 --> 01:18:09,251
Let me try the eel this time.

1984
01:18:10,452 --> 01:18:12,821
-You said it tasted strong, right?
-Yes.

1985
01:18:13,488 --> 01:18:14,956
The sweetness and saltiness were strong.

1986
01:18:15,023 --> 01:18:15,957
HMM?

1987
01:18:16,024 --> 01:18:19,394
Try the ginger, pepper, and green onion

1988
01:18:19,461 --> 01:18:21,730
-all at once.
-Okay.

1989
01:18:21,797 --> 01:18:25,067
-That's… With green onion.
-Green onion.

1990
01:18:25,600 --> 01:18:27,169
I hope everything is cooked well.

1991
01:18:27,235 --> 01:18:28,870
ALL IN ONE BITE

1992
01:18:28,937 --> 01:18:30,272
This time, the green onion.

1993
01:18:32,140 --> 01:18:33,575
DAE-MYUNG IN ANTICIPATION

1994
01:18:35,143 --> 01:18:36,478
It looks like

1995
01:18:36,545 --> 01:18:41,383
Dae-myung's review from the previous round
had an impact on him.

1996
01:18:41,450 --> 01:18:44,619
-No, I wasn't thinking about that.
-You weren't?

1997
01:18:44,686 --> 01:18:48,423
First, because Chef Nam-no's dish
came with this sauce,

1998
01:18:48,490 --> 01:18:52,694
I thought the sauce would have
a very strong taste.

1999
01:18:52,761 --> 01:18:57,365
But it tasted
luxurious and smooth instead.

2000
01:18:57,432 --> 01:19:00,902
That was an unexpected twist.

2001
01:19:00,969 --> 01:19:04,439
Overall, the dish was fantastic
and delicious.

2002
01:19:04,506 --> 01:19:05,807
And now,

2003
01:19:05,874 --> 01:19:08,744
I'll try Chef Sung-jun's dish
and see how they compare.

2004
01:19:08,810 --> 01:19:10,212
Compare them right away.

2005
01:19:10,278 --> 01:19:11,813
How can I put this?

2006
01:19:11,880 --> 01:19:15,250
I can't really think of
a specific location.

2007
01:19:15,317 --> 01:19:20,021
-I'm sorry, I can only say it like this.
-Do it in your own style.

2008
01:19:20,088 --> 01:19:21,156
I'm sorry.

2009
01:19:21,223 --> 01:19:23,892
That's Chef Sung-jun's dish,

2010
01:19:23,959 --> 01:19:25,026
Ugly Namkoong Min.

2011
01:19:25,093 --> 01:19:27,596
A PERFECT SHORTCUT TO UGLINESS,
CARBS AND SALTINESS IN DOENJANG PASTA

2012
01:19:28,530 --> 01:19:33,568
FINISH WITH THE SWEET POTATO CRÈME BRÛLÉE

2013
01:19:34,136 --> 01:19:38,206
CHEF KWON SUNG-JUN'S UGLY NAMKOONG MIN

2014
01:19:38,273 --> 01:19:40,642
-I'll just let him taste it.
-What?

2015
01:19:40,709 --> 01:19:42,377
The black sesame biscuit.

2016
01:19:42,444 --> 01:19:46,748
Did you get those ready?
Don't let it affect your evaluation.

2017
01:19:46,815 --> 01:19:48,850
-He should've served these in time.
-I see.

2018
01:19:48,917 --> 01:19:51,219
Should I mix everything?

2019
01:19:51,286 --> 01:19:52,988
Yes, mix it lightly and try it.

2020
01:19:53,054 --> 01:19:54,790
-It's also a hangover cure.
-It is?

2021
01:19:54,856 --> 01:19:58,226
-I'll mix it and have a bite.
-He's mixing.

2022
01:19:58,293 --> 01:20:02,898
Unlike the dish's name, Ugly Namkoong Min,

2023
01:20:02,964 --> 01:20:05,433
everything looks really pretty.

2024
01:20:05,500 --> 01:20:07,235
-Look at the <i>doenjang</i> pasta.
-It's <i>doenjang-sulbap.</i>

2025
01:20:07,302 --> 01:20:08,270
Is the pasta cooked?

2026
01:20:08,336 --> 01:20:10,105
It looks pretty classy.

2027
01:20:10,172 --> 01:20:14,376
-Let me scoop up a huge spoonful.
-It must be hot.

2028
01:20:14,876 --> 01:20:17,012
TAKING A HUGE BITE

2029
01:20:19,848 --> 01:20:21,283
BOTH HANDS CLASPED

2030
01:20:25,854 --> 01:20:27,389
SLOWLY TURNS HIS HEAD TOWARD THE CHEF

2031
01:20:27,455 --> 01:20:29,925
-He turns slowly.
-He turns toward Sung-jun with every chew.

2032
01:20:29,991 --> 01:20:31,660
That's scary.

2033
01:20:31,726 --> 01:20:33,395
-It was scary.
-I'm scared.

2034
01:20:33,995 --> 01:20:35,263
He seems to enjoy it.

2035
01:20:35,330 --> 01:20:38,834
His eyes tell so many stories.

2036
01:20:38,900 --> 01:20:40,669
It looks delicious.

2037
01:20:40,735 --> 01:20:42,637
I think it'll hit him more intuitively.

2038
01:20:42,704 --> 01:20:45,207
How well is the pasta cooked?

2039
01:20:45,273 --> 01:20:48,543
It doesn't even feel like pasta.

2040
01:20:48,610 --> 01:20:50,178
-Rice?
-Rice?

2041
01:20:50,245 --> 01:20:51,880
It's light,

2042
01:20:51,947 --> 01:20:56,318
<i>but it hits me here and there</i>
<i>with strong and rich flavors.</i>

2043
01:20:56,384 --> 01:20:59,454
But it also had a refreshing

2044
01:20:59,521 --> 01:21:02,224
and a relieving kind of flavor.

2045
01:21:02,290 --> 01:21:03,992
Do you think you'll look bloated tomorrow?

2046
01:21:04,059 --> 01:21:06,027
Tomorrow? Oh, yes.

2047
01:21:06,094 --> 01:21:07,896
I'll look very ugly tomorrow.

2048
01:21:07,963 --> 01:21:10,932
-It must taste pretty strong.
-It does.

2049
01:21:10,999 --> 01:21:12,367
-He moves on right away.
-Yes.

2050
01:21:12,434 --> 01:21:14,202
Do I just eat it like this?

2051
01:21:14,269 --> 01:21:15,937
Yes, that's called crème brûlée,

2052
01:21:16,004 --> 01:21:19,975
<i>made with sweet potato,</i>
<i>egg, and almond milk.</i>

2053
01:21:20,041 --> 01:21:20,942
Crème brûlée.

2054
01:21:21,009 --> 01:21:24,279
It looks sweet.
He used lots of sugar too, right?

2055
01:21:24,346 --> 01:21:27,449
-It must be a bit sweet.
-Something sweet after a salty dish.

2056
01:21:27,515 --> 01:21:29,284
He's showing a nice smile.

2057
01:21:29,351 --> 01:21:32,554
-That's not a part of the cook-off.
-Finish the meal with the sesame tuile.

2058
01:21:33,255 --> 01:21:34,990
He couldn't serve it in time,

2059
01:21:35,056 --> 01:21:37,025
but you can feel free to try it.

2060
01:21:37,092 --> 01:21:38,960
-Yes.
-Yes?

2061
01:21:39,027 --> 01:21:40,161
It's delicious.

2062
01:21:40,962 --> 01:21:43,331
THE DESSERT IS A PASS TOO

2063
01:21:43,398 --> 01:21:47,068
-Nam-no's dish.
-He goes back to the dishes again.

2064
01:21:49,004 --> 01:21:50,772
NODS♥

2065
01:21:50,839 --> 01:21:52,774
It's so good.

2066
01:21:52,841 --> 01:21:54,643
Both of them…

2067
01:21:54,709 --> 01:21:56,411
Why did you give such a good review?

2068
01:21:57,545 --> 01:21:59,915
Both of you

2069
01:21:59,981 --> 01:22:03,485
didn't make something ugly,
but something so pretty

2070
01:22:03,551 --> 01:22:05,053
and even tastes good.

2071
01:22:05,120 --> 01:22:07,522
So I'm a bit split right now,

2072
01:22:07,589 --> 01:22:09,991
but I'll think about it
and make a wise choice.

2073
01:22:10,058 --> 01:22:14,529
Please try Yoon Nam-No Handsome first.

2074
01:22:14,763 --> 01:22:16,331
YUM

2075
01:22:19,567 --> 01:22:21,036
YUM

2076
01:22:21,102 --> 01:22:22,604
There's eel too.

2077
01:22:22,671 --> 01:22:23,905
CONTINUES TO EAT

2078
01:22:23,972 --> 01:22:25,540
Gosh, this is good.

2079
01:22:25,974 --> 01:22:28,510
AMAZED FIRST, DEVOUR LATER

2080
01:22:28,576 --> 01:22:29,978
SLURP

2081
01:22:30,979 --> 01:22:32,580
A BITE OF THE GREEN ONION

2082
01:22:35,283 --> 01:22:36,518
CLEANED OUT IN NO TIME

2083
01:22:36,584 --> 01:22:37,919
Gosh.

2084
01:22:37,986 --> 01:22:39,654
This soy-based sauce is really good.

2085
01:22:39,721 --> 01:22:42,757
It tastes similar
to a dish called <i>kakuni</i> in Japan,

2086
01:22:42,824 --> 01:22:45,093
and it's like Japanese-style Dongpo pork,

2087
01:22:45,160 --> 01:22:48,830
made by cooking it in soy sauce
for two hours to make it tender.

2088
01:22:48,897 --> 01:22:50,899
But he managed to create the flavor
this quickly.

2089
01:22:50,966 --> 01:22:55,337
He finished this in 15 minutes
when it actually takes 2 hours.

2090
01:22:55,403 --> 01:22:57,772
The glass noodles got wet,
so they weren't crispy,

2091
01:22:57,839 --> 01:23:00,108
but it absorbed all the sauce,

2092
01:23:00,175 --> 01:23:02,811
so eating that was
the biggest kick for this dish.

2093
01:23:02,877 --> 01:23:05,513
You can easily get bloated
by eating glass noodles for breakfast.

2094
01:23:06,848 --> 01:23:08,416
I think he did a good job.

2095
01:23:08,984 --> 01:23:12,654
Most of the cast members wait
until the guest gives their review,

2096
01:23:12,721 --> 01:23:15,223
but they're scared of his eloquence.

2097
01:23:15,290 --> 01:23:17,058
We have to get it done first.

2098
01:23:17,125 --> 01:23:19,661
There's no way we can do any better
if we go after him.

2099
01:23:19,728 --> 01:23:22,797
-You'd get compared to him.
-Everyone, review it now.

2100
01:23:22,864 --> 01:23:25,734
If you want to say something, go now.
Chef Jong-won, do you want to go?

2101
01:23:25,800 --> 01:23:28,236
I feel like I'm in Hongdae.

2102
01:23:28,303 --> 01:23:30,138
-He went to Hongdae.
-He's in Hongdae.

2103
01:23:30,205 --> 01:23:32,073
Once I get wasted,

2104
01:23:32,140 --> 01:23:36,011
I can probably eat this forever
with some warmed instant rice.

2105
01:23:36,077 --> 01:23:37,078
-Is that so?
-It's good.

2106
01:23:37,145 --> 01:23:39,047
Dae-myung, what do you think?

2107
01:23:39,114 --> 01:23:39,981
DAE-MYUNG'S TURN!

2108
01:23:41,449 --> 01:23:42,484
In my mouth,

2109
01:23:44,019 --> 01:23:45,687
an orchestra begins to play.

2110
01:23:45,920 --> 01:23:47,255
THERE'S HIS REVIEW

2111
01:23:47,322 --> 01:23:51,893
-An orchestra.
-Concerts mostly begin with soft music,

2112
01:23:51,960 --> 01:23:54,796
-but this begins with a big drum.
-The big drums?

2113
01:23:54,863 --> 01:23:56,898
I was first hit with the strong flavor,

2114
01:23:56,965 --> 01:23:59,367
followed by a string
of sweetness and sourness.

2115
01:23:59,434 --> 01:24:03,204
Everything comes together.

2116
01:24:04,239 --> 01:24:06,574
And wow, it's so moving.

2117
01:24:06,641 --> 01:24:09,444
It felt like I just listened
to a nice symphony.

2118
01:24:09,511 --> 01:24:12,280
-That means…
-This looks like Beethoven's hair.

2119
01:24:12,614 --> 01:24:14,449
PIG-THOVEN

2120
01:24:14,516 --> 01:24:17,585
-So it was good, right?
-Very much so.

2121
01:24:17,652 --> 01:24:19,954
Sorry to ask, but you'll review like this
next episode too, right?

2122
01:24:20,021 --> 01:24:21,423
Of course.

2123
01:24:21,956 --> 01:24:24,159
Some people come prepared, then…

2124
01:24:24,225 --> 01:24:27,862
-Then they run out of lines.
-He even admitted that.

2125
01:24:27,929 --> 01:24:29,030
But you say what comes to mind.

2126
01:24:29,097 --> 01:24:31,066
-It's really good.
-It is?

2127
01:24:31,132 --> 01:24:34,469
This time, let's try
Chef Sung-jun's Ugly Namkoong Min.

2128
01:24:37,806 --> 01:24:38,973
A BITE

2129
01:24:39,340 --> 01:24:41,709
This pasta is unique.

2130
01:24:42,110 --> 01:24:44,045
TRUDGES

2131
01:24:44,345 --> 01:24:45,547
AND STANDS IN FRONT OF THE POT

2132
01:24:46,381 --> 01:24:48,516
CHOMP… CHOMP… CHOMP…

2133
01:24:50,418 --> 01:24:52,554
Why are you eating
so much of your opponent's food?

2134
01:24:53,221 --> 01:24:54,422
It's hot.

2135
01:24:55,657 --> 01:24:57,492
This can make you bloated to death.

2136
01:24:57,992 --> 01:25:00,028
-You can't wake up after eating this.
-Or open your eyes.

2137
01:25:00,095 --> 01:25:02,464
-It feels like barley rice too.
-It does.

2138
01:25:02,530 --> 01:25:04,532
-And tastes like it.
-Barley rice. Yes.

2139
01:25:04,599 --> 01:25:06,568
-Or corn.
-Corn porridge.

2140
01:25:06,634 --> 01:25:08,837
It's like corn porridge, right?
From the old days.

2141
01:25:09,204 --> 01:25:11,706
SNIFFLING IN HIS MEMORIES…

2142
01:25:11,773 --> 01:25:12,941
That was his staple.

2143
01:25:13,007 --> 01:25:16,411
-The grains were bigger.
-Are they? I don't really know.

2144
01:25:16,478 --> 01:25:19,080
-It feels like barley rice.
-The texture is quite similar.

2145
01:25:19,147 --> 01:25:21,916
Yes, it doesn't taste bland.

2146
01:25:21,983 --> 01:25:24,185
Are you done? Any thoughts?

2147
01:25:24,252 --> 01:25:25,553
TIME FOR DAE-MYUNG'S REVIEW!

2148
01:25:27,055 --> 01:25:27,989
Well…

2149
01:25:28,056 --> 01:25:29,824
You already used an orchestra.

2150
01:25:29,891 --> 01:25:31,993
-There was this man.
-There was a man.

2151
01:25:32,327 --> 01:25:34,662
THE INTRO IS ALREADY EXTRAORDINARY

2152
01:25:35,230 --> 01:25:37,565
His dream was to propose

2153
01:25:37,632 --> 01:25:41,569
to the woman he loved
by putting the ring in <i>doenjang-jjigae.</i>

2154
01:25:41,803 --> 01:25:42,804
SO INTERESTING

2155
01:25:42,871 --> 01:25:44,873
-That's me.
-But this <i>doenjang-jjigae</i>

2156
01:25:44,939 --> 01:25:46,541
was way too delicious.

2157
01:25:46,608 --> 01:25:49,177
So I think the proposal won't go well.

2158
01:25:49,244 --> 01:25:51,513
-Will Sung-jun take her?
-Did she swallow it?

2159
01:25:51,579 --> 01:25:53,648
She would've eaten the ring too.

2160
01:25:54,082 --> 01:25:55,884
IS THAT A GOOD THING?

2161
01:25:56,451 --> 01:25:58,586
LIKE THIS

2162
01:25:58,653 --> 01:26:02,790
-If he proposes with this <i>jjigae…</i>
-It can't be too good.

2163
01:26:02,857 --> 01:26:04,559
…he'd likely fail.

2164
01:26:04,626 --> 01:26:05,994
This is that good.

2165
01:26:06,060 --> 01:26:07,529
-Even the ring.
-The failed proposal.

2166
01:26:08,963 --> 01:26:10,365
-All right.
-Time to decide.

2167
01:26:10,431 --> 01:26:12,000
It's now your turn to decide.

2168
01:26:12,066 --> 01:26:14,569
<i>Press one for Yoon Nam-no. One for Nam-no.</i>

2169
01:26:14,636 --> 01:26:16,571
<i>Or press two for Kwon Sung-jun.</i>

2170
01:26:16,638 --> 01:26:19,941
I'm not sure
whether it's a good thing to win.

2171
01:26:20,008 --> 01:26:23,044
The one who gets chosen
is the epitome of ugliness.

2172
01:26:23,111 --> 01:26:24,279
Do you understand?

2173
01:26:24,345 --> 01:26:25,813
It will be sealed.

2174
01:26:25,880 --> 01:26:27,749
Please press a button.

2175
01:26:27,815 --> 01:26:29,250
-Did you?
-I did.

2176
01:26:29,317 --> 01:26:32,987
Who will be the one
to complete The Ugliness?

2177
01:26:33,054 --> 01:26:35,290
Let's find out who he chose.

2178
01:26:35,356 --> 01:26:36,357
Show us!

2179
01:26:37,659 --> 01:26:39,861
The Ugliness.

2180
01:26:39,928 --> 01:26:43,932
If Sung-jun wins this round,
it'll be his fifth win in a row.

2181
01:26:43,998 --> 01:26:45,400
He's on a roll.

2182
01:26:45,466 --> 01:26:48,269
If Nam-no wins against him,

2183
01:26:48,336 --> 01:26:51,072
it may mark the beginning of his comeback.

2184
01:26:51,139 --> 01:26:53,441
Which one of them suits the phrase
The Ugliness better?

2185
01:26:53,508 --> 01:26:56,211
Is it Sung-jun or Nam-no?

2186
01:26:56,277 --> 01:26:58,813
Who did Min choose? Who won?

2187
01:26:59,414 --> 01:27:00,481
Show us!

2188
01:27:01,182 --> 01:27:02,250
The winner is…

2189
01:27:02,317 --> 01:27:03,284
KWON SUNG-JUN WINS

2190
01:27:03,351 --> 01:27:04,385
Sung-jun wins!

2191
01:27:04,452 --> 01:27:07,155
-What? I won?
-Sung-jun wins!

2192
01:27:07,222 --> 01:27:08,423
KWON SUNG-JUN, THE UGLY

2193
01:27:08,489 --> 01:27:10,959
-Wait.
-Sung-jun wins five times in a row.

2194
01:27:11,025 --> 01:27:13,027
-How ugly.
-You're now The Ugliness.

2195
01:27:13,094 --> 01:27:15,163
-Is this a good thing?
-The Ugliness.

2196
01:27:15,430 --> 01:27:17,332
CONGRATULATIONS

2197
01:27:18,333 --> 01:27:19,367
It's a good thing.

2198
01:27:19,434 --> 01:27:20,969
So I'm the king?

2199
01:27:21,035 --> 01:27:23,404
-You're King Ugly.
-The cherry on top.

2200
01:27:23,471 --> 01:27:25,039
It seemed

2201
01:27:25,106 --> 01:27:29,277
somewhat rich and bold,
yet it tasted light at the same time.

2202
01:27:29,344 --> 01:27:32,614
And when I had
the sweet potato dish right here,

2203
01:27:32,680 --> 01:27:38,052
it had a smooth and sweet flavor,
unlike the other dish.

2204
01:27:38,119 --> 01:27:40,555
-That balance was really delicious.
-I get it.

2205
01:27:40,622 --> 01:27:44,959
-Thank you for making Ugly Namkoong Min.
-He chose Ugly Namkoong Min.

2206
01:27:47,328 --> 01:27:49,864
Sung-jun, this is your fifth win in a row.

2207
01:27:49,931 --> 01:27:51,466
-Any thoughts?
-Five in a row?

2208
01:27:51,532 --> 01:27:52,634
It feels great

2209
01:27:53,201 --> 01:27:54,302
with a hint of irritation.

2210
01:27:54,569 --> 01:27:56,137
THE FINAL FORM OF UGLINESS!

2211
01:27:56,204 --> 01:27:58,106
You have completed ugliness.

2212
01:27:58,172 --> 01:28:00,908
Yes, I turned out to be
the final form of ugliness.

2213
01:28:00,975 --> 01:28:03,578
But still, I'm glad I've won
five times in a row. Thank you.

2214
01:28:03,645 --> 01:28:06,080
THANK YOU FOR THE 5TH WIN IN A ROW

2215
01:28:06,147 --> 01:28:08,616
He's on a sweeping upturn
with his five-game winning streak!

2216
01:28:08,683 --> 01:28:12,186
This puts Sung-jun at six stars.

2217
01:28:12,253 --> 01:28:16,124
He has surpassed Hyun-suk in the ranks

2218
01:28:16,190 --> 01:28:18,393
and goes up one!

2219
01:28:18,459 --> 01:28:21,262
Hyun-suk now stands beneath Sung-jun.

2220
01:28:21,329 --> 01:28:23,998
It's your sixth win, Sung-jun!
Congratulations.

2221
01:28:24,932 --> 01:28:26,968
He's famous as a foodie
in the entertainment business.

2222
01:28:27,035 --> 01:28:29,070
I don't drink a lot of soju in one place.

2223
01:28:29,137 --> 01:28:30,204
I hop seven or eight times.

2224
01:28:30,271 --> 01:28:31,406
RESTAURANT-HOPS 7 TO 8 TIMES

2225
01:28:31,472 --> 01:28:33,107
It's like going on a day trip.

2226
01:28:33,174 --> 01:28:34,542
Any good places you can share?

2227
01:28:34,609 --> 01:28:36,311
In Seochon…

2228
01:28:36,377 --> 01:28:38,246
In Yeonsinnae…

2229
01:28:38,313 --> 01:28:39,347
It was so delicious.

2230
01:28:39,414 --> 01:28:40,715
-You'd crave that.
-I want to go.

2231
01:28:40,782 --> 01:28:42,383
We present Dae-myung's fridge!

2232
01:28:43,584 --> 01:28:44,919
It's from a <i>bugeo-guk</i> place.

2233
01:28:44,986 --> 01:28:46,688
There's a butcher shop in Yaksu-dong.

2234
01:28:46,754 --> 01:28:48,156
When you have a bite with closed eyes,

2235
01:28:48,222 --> 01:28:49,791
-you're already in paradise.
-He knows.

2236
01:28:49,857 --> 01:28:51,459
You're a foodie.

2237
01:28:51,526 --> 01:28:53,127
Let us begin

2238
01:28:53,194 --> 01:28:55,630
the 15-minute cook-off to move Dae-myung!

2239
01:28:55,863 --> 01:28:57,065
TODAY'S DESTINATION,

2240
01:28:57,131 --> 01:28:57,965
A DELICIOUS PLACE!

2241
01:28:58,232 --> 01:28:59,133
EXCITED♥

2242
01:28:59,434 --> 01:29:00,368
TASTY FULL-COURSE MEALS

2243
01:29:00,601 --> 01:29:01,536
FROM ALL AROUND THE WORLD

2244
01:29:01,602 --> 01:29:02,470
What's that?

2245
01:29:02,537 --> 01:29:03,638
How's that authentic Mexican?

2246
01:29:03,705 --> 01:29:04,906
Sanchez told me to do this.

2247
01:29:05,173 --> 01:29:06,307
APPROVED BY A LOCAL?

2248
01:29:06,574 --> 01:29:08,376
TAKING OFF WITH A BITE

2249
01:29:09,544 --> 01:29:10,445
ARRIVED IN JAPAN

2250
01:29:10,511 --> 01:29:12,180
There's a salsa party in my mouth.

2251
01:29:13,548 --> 01:29:14,849
HERE'S ANOTHER TOURIST

2252
01:29:15,283 --> 01:29:17,652
HOW FAR WILL
THE OVERLY-IMMERSIVE FOOD TOUR GO?

2253
01:29:29,063 --> 01:29:33,835
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
